108static bool isTransformTypeTransformationMatrix(TransformOperation::OperationType transformType)
109{
110 switch (transformType) {
111 case TransformOperation::SKEW_X:
112 case TransformOperation::SKEW_Y:
113 case TransformOperation::SKEW:
114 case TransformOperation::MATRIX:
115 case TransformOperation::ROTATE_3D:
116 case TransformOperation::MATRIX_3D:
117 case TransformOperation::PERSPECTIVE:
118 case TransformOperation::IDENTITY:
119 case TransformOperation::NONE:
120 return true;
121 default:
122 return false;
123 }
124}
125
126static bool isTransformTypeFloatPoint3D(TransformOperation::OperationType transformType)
127{
128 switch (transformType) {
129 case TransformOperation::SCALE:
130 case TransformOperation::SCALE_3D:
131 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE:
132 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_3D:
133 return true;
134 default:
135 return false;
136 }
137}
138
139static bool isTransformTypeNumber(TransformOperation::OperationType transformType)
140{
141 return !isTransformTypeTransformationMatrix(transformType) && !isTransformTypeFloatPoint3D(transformType);
142}
143
144static void getTransformFunctionValue(const TransformOperation* transformOp, TransformOperation::OperationType transformType, const FloatSize& size, float& value)
145{
146 switch (transformType) {
147 case TransformOperation::ROTATE:
148 case TransformOperation::ROTATE_X:
149 case TransformOperation::ROTATE_Y:
150 value = transformOp ? narrowPrecisionToFloat(deg2rad(downcast<RotateTransformOperation>(*transformOp).angle())) : 0;
151 break;
152 case TransformOperation::SCALE_X:
153 value = transformOp ? narrowPrecisionToFloat(downcast<ScaleTransformOperation>(*transformOp).x()) : 1;
154 break;
155 case TransformOperation::SCALE_Y:
156 value = transformOp ? narrowPrecisionToFloat(downcast<ScaleTransformOperation>(*transformOp).y()) : 1;
157 break;
158 case TransformOperation::SCALE_Z:
159 value = transformOp ? narrowPrecisionToFloat(downcast<ScaleTransformOperation>(*transformOp).z()) : 1;
160 break;
161 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_X:
162 value = transformOp ? downcast<TranslateTransformOperation>(*transformOp).xAsFloat(size) : 0;
163 break;
164 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_Y:
165 value = transformOp ? downcast<TranslateTransformOperation>(*transformOp).yAsFloat(size) : 0;
166 break;
167 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_Z:
168 value = transformOp ? downcast<TranslateTransformOperation>(*transformOp).zAsFloat() : 0;
169 break;
170 default:
171 break;
172 }
173}
174
175static void getTransformFunctionValue(const TransformOperation* transformOp, TransformOperation::OperationType transformType, const FloatSize& size, FloatPoint3D& value)
176{
177 switch (transformType) {
178 case TransformOperation::SCALE:
179 case TransformOperation::SCALE_3D: {
180 const auto* scaleTransformOp = downcast<ScaleTransformOperation>(transformOp);
181 value.setX(scaleTransformOp ? narrowPrecisionToFloat(scaleTransformOp->x()) : 1);
182 value.setY(scaleTransformOp ? narrowPrecisionToFloat(scaleTransformOp->y()) : 1);
183 value.setZ(scaleTransformOp ? narrowPrecisionToFloat(scaleTransformOp->z()) : 1);
184 break;
185 }
186 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE:
187 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_3D: {
188 const auto* translateTransformOp = downcast<TranslateTransformOperation>(transformOp);
189 value.setX(translateTransformOp ? translateTransformOp->xAsFloat(size) : 0);
190 value.setY(translateTransformOp ? translateTransformOp->yAsFloat(size) : 0);
191 value.setZ(translateTransformOp ? translateTransformOp->zAsFloat() : 0);
192 break;
193 }
194 default:
195 break;
196 }
197}
198
199static void getTransformFunctionValue(const TransformOperation* transformOp, TransformOperation::OperationType transformType, const FloatSize& size, TransformationMatrix& value)
200{
201 switch (transformType) {
202 case TransformOperation::SKEW_X:
203 case TransformOperation::SKEW_Y:
204 case TransformOperation::SKEW:
205 case TransformOperation::MATRIX:
206 case TransformOperation::ROTATE_3D:
207 case TransformOperation::MATRIX_3D:
208 case TransformOperation::PERSPECTIVE:
209 case TransformOperation::IDENTITY:
210 case TransformOperation::NONE:
211 if (transformOp)
212 transformOp->apply(value, size);
213 else
214 value.makeIdentity();
215 break;
216 default:
217 break;
218 }
219}

221static PlatformCAAnimation::ValueFunctionType getValueFunctionNameForTransformOperation(TransformOperation::OperationType transformType)
222{
223 // Use literal strings to avoid link-time dependency on those symbols.
224 switch (transformType) {
225 case TransformOperation::ROTATE_X:
226 return PlatformCAAnimation::RotateX;
227 case TransformOperation::ROTATE_Y:
228 return PlatformCAAnimation::RotateY;
229 case TransformOperation::ROTATE:
230 return PlatformCAAnimation::RotateZ;
231 case TransformOperation::SCALE_X:
232 return PlatformCAAnimation::ScaleX;
233 case TransformOperation::SCALE_Y:
234 return PlatformCAAnimation::ScaleY;
235 case TransformOperation::SCALE_Z:
236 return PlatformCAAnimation::ScaleZ;
237 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_X:
238 return PlatformCAAnimation::TranslateX;
239 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_Y:
240 return PlatformCAAnimation::TranslateY;
241 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_Z:
242 return PlatformCAAnimation::TranslateZ;
243 case TransformOperation::SCALE:
244 case TransformOperation::SCALE_3D:
245 return PlatformCAAnimation::Scale;
246 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE:
247 case TransformOperation::TRANSLATE_3D:
248 return PlatformCAAnimation::Translate;
249 default:
250 return PlatformCAAnimation::NoValueFunction;
251 }
252}

254static ASCIILiteral propertyIdToString(AnimatedPropertyID property)
255{
256 switch (property) {
257 case AnimatedPropertyTranslate:
258 case AnimatedPropertyScale:
259 case AnimatedPropertyRotate:
260 case AnimatedPropertyTransform:
261 return "transform"_s;
262 case AnimatedPropertyOpacity:
263 return "opacity"_s;
264 case AnimatedPropertyBackgroundColor:
265 return "backgroundColor"_s;
266 case AnimatedPropertyFilter:
267 return "filters"_s;
268#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
269 case AnimatedPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter:
270 return "backdropFilters"_s;
271#endif
272 case AnimatedPropertyInvalid:
273 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
274 }
275 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
276 return ASCIILiteral::null();
277}

279static bool animationHasStepsTimingFunction(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const Animation* anim)
280{
281 if (is<StepsTimingFunction>(anim->timingFunction()))
282 return true;
283
284 bool hasStepsDefaultTimingFunctionForKeyframes = is<StepsTimingFunction>(anim->defaultTimingFunctionForKeyframes());
285 for (unsigned i = 0; i < valueList.size(); ++i) {
286 if (const TimingFunction* timingFunction = valueList.at(i).timingFunction()) {
287 if (is<StepsTimingFunction>(timingFunction))
288 return true;
289 } else if (hasStepsDefaultTimingFunctionForKeyframes)
290 return true;
291 }
292
293 return false;
294}

305bool GraphicsLayer::supportsLayerType(Type type)
306{
307 switch (type) {
308 case Type::Normal:
309 case Type::PageTiledBacking:
310 case Type::ScrollContainer:
311 case Type::ScrolledContents:
312 return true;
313 case Type::Shape:
314#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
315 // FIXME: we can use shaper layers on Windows when PlatformCALayerCocoa::setShapePath() etc are implemented.
316 return true;
317#else
318 return false;
319#endif
320 }
321 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
322 return false;
323}

344Ref<GraphicsLayer> GraphicsLayer::create(GraphicsLayerFactory* factory, GraphicsLayerClient& client, Type layerType)
345{
346 if (factory) {
347 auto layer = factory->createGraphicsLayer(layerType, client);
348 layer->initialize(layerType);
349 return layer;
350 }
351
352 auto layer = adoptRef(*new GraphicsLayerCA(layerType, client));
353 layer->initialize(layerType);
354 return WTFMove(layer);
355}

426void GraphicsLayerCA::initialize(Type layerType)
427{
428 PlatformCALayer::LayerType platformLayerType;
429 switch (layerType) {
430 case Type::Normal:
431 case Type::ScrolledContents:
432 platformLayerType = PlatformCALayer::LayerType::LayerTypeWebLayer;
433 break;
434 case Type::PageTiledBacking:
435 platformLayerType = PlatformCALayer::LayerType::LayerTypePageTiledBackingLayer;
436 break;
437 case Type::ScrollContainer:
438 platformLayerType = PlatformCALayer::LayerType::LayerTypeScrollContainerLayer;
439 break;
440 case Type::Shape:
441 platformLayerType = PlatformCALayer::LayerType::LayerTypeShapeLayer;
442 break;
443 }
444 m_layer = createPlatformCALayer(platformLayerType, this);
445 noteLayerPropertyChanged(ContentsScaleChanged);
446 noteLayerPropertyChanged(CoverageRectChanged);
447}
448
449GraphicsLayerCA::~GraphicsLayerCA()
450{
451 if (UNLIKELY(isTrackingDisplayListReplay()))
452 layerDisplayListMap().remove(this);
453
454 // We release our references to the PlatformCALayers here, but do not actively unparent them,
455 // since that will cause a commit and break our batched commit model. The layers will
456 // get released when the rootmost modified GraphicsLayerCA rebuilds its child layers.
457
458 // Clean up the layer.
459 if (m_layer)
460 m_layer->setOwner(nullptr);
461
462 if (m_contentsLayer)
463 m_contentsLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
464
465 if (m_contentsClippingLayer)
466 m_contentsClippingLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
467
468 if (m_contentsShapeMaskLayer)
469 m_contentsShapeMaskLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
470
471 if (m_shapeMaskLayer)
472 m_shapeMaskLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
473
474 if (m_structuralLayer)
475 m_structuralLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
476
477 if (m_backdropLayer)
478 m_backdropLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
479
480 if (m_backdropClippingLayer)
481 m_backdropClippingLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
482
483 removeCloneLayers();
484
485 if (m_parent)
486 downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*m_parent).noteSublayersChanged();
487
488 willBeDestroyed();
489}

687void GraphicsLayerCA::moveOrCopyLayerAnimation(MoveOrCopy operation, const String& animationIdentifier, std::optional<Seconds> beginTime, PlatformCALayer *fromLayer, PlatformCALayer *toLayer)
688{
689 RefPtr<PlatformCAAnimation> anim = fromLayer->animationForKey(animationIdentifier);
690 if (!anim)
691 return;
692
693 if (beginTime && beginTime->seconds() != anim->beginTime())
694 anim->setBeginTime(beginTime->seconds());
695
696 switch (operation) {
697 case Move:
698 fromLayer->removeAnimationForKey(animationIdentifier);
699 toLayer->addAnimationForKey(animationIdentifier, *anim);
700 break;
701
702 case Copy:
703 toLayer->addAnimationForKey(animationIdentifier, *anim);
704 break;
705 }
706}
707
708void GraphicsLayerCA::moveOrCopyAnimations(MoveOrCopy operation, PlatformCALayer *fromLayer, PlatformCALayer *toLayer)
709{
710 for (auto& animationGroup : m_animationGroups) {
711 if ((animatedPropertyIsTransformOrRelated(animationGroup.m_property)
712 || animationGroup.m_property == AnimatedPropertyOpacity
713 || animationGroup.m_property == AnimatedPropertyBackgroundColor
714 || animationGroup.m_property == AnimatedPropertyFilter))
715 moveOrCopyLayerAnimation(operation, animationGroup.animationIdentifier(), animationGroup.computedBeginTime(), fromLayer, toLayer);
716 }
717}

865bool GraphicsLayerCA::setFilters(const FilterOperations& filterOperations)
866{
867 bool canCompositeFilters = filtersCanBeComposited(filterOperations);
868
869 if (m_filters == filterOperations)
870 return canCompositeFilters;
871
872 // Filters cause flattening, so we should never have filters on a layer with preserves3D().
873 ASSERT(!filterOperations.size() || !preserves3D());
874
875 if (canCompositeFilters) {
876 GraphicsLayer::setFilters(filterOperations);
877 noteLayerPropertyChanged(FiltersChanged);
878 } else if (filters().size()) {
879 // In this case filters are rendered in software, so we need to remove any
880 // previously attached hardware filters.
881 clearFilters();
882 noteLayerPropertyChanged(FiltersChanged);
883 }
884 return canCompositeFilters;
885}
886
887bool GraphicsLayerCA::setBackdropFilters(const FilterOperations& filterOperations)
888{
889 bool canCompositeFilters = filtersCanBeComposited(filterOperations);
890
891 if (m_backdropFilters == filterOperations)
892 return canCompositeFilters;
893
894 // Filters cause flattening, so we should never have filters on a layer with preserves3D().
895 ASSERT(!filterOperations.size() || !preserves3D());
896
897 if (canCompositeFilters)
898 GraphicsLayer::setBackdropFilters(filterOperations);
899 else {
900 // FIXME: This would clear the backdrop filters if we had a software implementation.
901 clearBackdropFilters();
902 }
903
904 noteLayerPropertyChanged(BackdropFiltersChanged | DebugIndicatorsChanged);
905 return canCompositeFilters;
906}

938void GraphicsLayerCA::setNeedsDisplay()
939{
940 if (!drawsContent())
941 return;
942
943 m_needsFullRepaint = true;
944 m_dirtyRects.clear();
945 noteLayerPropertyChanged(DirtyRectsChanged);
946 addRepaintRect(FloatRect(FloatPoint(), m_size));
947}
948
949void GraphicsLayerCA::setNeedsDisplayInRect(const FloatRect& r, ShouldClipToLayer shouldClip)
950{
951 if (!drawsContent())
952 return;
953
954 if (m_needsFullRepaint)
955 return;
956
957 FloatRect rect(r);
958 if (shouldClip == ClipToLayer) {
959 FloatRect layerBounds(FloatPoint(), m_size);
960 rect.intersect(layerBounds);
961 }
962
963 if (rect.isEmpty())
964 return;
965
966 addRepaintRect(rect);
967
968 const size_t maxDirtyRects = 32;
969
970 for (size_t i = 0; i < m_dirtyRects.size(); ++i) {
971 if (m_dirtyRects[i].contains(rect))
972 return;
973 }
974
975 if (m_dirtyRects.size() < maxDirtyRects)
976 m_dirtyRects.append(rect);
977 else
978 m_dirtyRects[0].unite(rect);
979
980 noteLayerPropertyChanged(DirtyRectsChanged);
981}

1072
1073static bool timingFunctionIsCubicTimingFunctionWithYValueOutOfRange(const TimingFunction* timingFunction)
1074{
1075 if (!is<CubicBezierTimingFunction>(timingFunction))
1076 return false;
1077
1078 auto yValueIsOutOfRange = [](double y) -> bool {
1079 return y < 0 || y > 1;
1080 };
1081
1082 auto& cubicBezierTimingFunction = downcast<CubicBezierTimingFunction>(*timingFunction);
1083 return yValueIsOutOfRange(cubicBezierTimingFunction.y1()) || yValueIsOutOfRange(cubicBezierTimingFunction.y2());
1084}
1085
1086static bool keyframeValueListHasSingleIntervalWithLinearOrEquivalentTimingFunction(const KeyframeValueList& valueList)
1087{
1088 if (valueList.size() != 2)
1089 return false;
1090
1091 auto* timingFunction = valueList.at(0).timingFunction();
1092 if (!timingFunction || is<LinearTimingFunction>(timingFunction))
1093 return true;
1094
1095 return is<CubicBezierTimingFunction>(timingFunction) && downcast<CubicBezierTimingFunction>(*timingFunction).isLinear();
1096}
1097
1098static bool animationCanBeAccelerated(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const Animation* anim)
1099{
1100 if (anim->playbackRate() != 1 || !anim->directionIsForwards())
1101 return false;
1102
1103 if (!anim || anim->isEmptyOrZeroDuration() || valueList.size() < 2)
1104 return false;
1105
1106 if (animationHasStepsTimingFunction(valueList, anim))
1107 return false;
1108
1109 return true;
1110}
1111
1112bool GraphicsLayerCA::addAnimation(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const FloatSize& boxSize, const Animation* anim, const String& animationName, double timeOffset)
1113{
1114 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << "GraphicsLayerCA " << this << " id " << primaryLayerID() << " addAnimation " << anim << " " << animationName << " duration " << anim->duration() << " (can be accelerated " << animationCanBeAccelerated(valueList, anim) << ")");
1115
1116 ASSERT(!animationName.isEmpty());
1117
1118 if (!animationCanBeAccelerated(valueList, anim))
1119 return false;
1120
1121 bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction = false;
1122 // Core Animation clips values outside of the [0-1] range for animation-wide cubic timing functions.
1123 if (timingFunctionIsCubicTimingFunctionWithYValueOutOfRange(anim->timingFunction())) {
1124 if (!keyframeValueListHasSingleIntervalWithLinearOrEquivalentTimingFunction(valueList))
1125 return false;
1126 keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction = true;
1127 }
1128
1129 bool createdAnimations = false;
1130 if (animatedPropertyIsTransformOrRelated(valueList.property()))
1131 createdAnimations = createTransformAnimationsFromKeyframes(valueList, anim, animationName, Seconds { timeOffset }, boxSize, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
1132 else if (valueList.property() == AnimatedPropertyFilter) {
1133 if (supportsAcceleratedFilterAnimations())
1134 createdAnimations = createFilterAnimationsFromKeyframes(valueList, anim, animationName, Seconds { timeOffset }, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
1135 }
1136#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
1137 else if (valueList.property() == AnimatedPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter) {
1138 if (supportsAcceleratedFilterAnimations())
1139 createdAnimations = createFilterAnimationsFromKeyframes(valueList, anim, animationName, Seconds { timeOffset }, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
1140 }
1141#endif
1142 else
1143 createdAnimations = createAnimationFromKeyframes(valueList, anim, animationName, Seconds { timeOffset }, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
1144
1145 if (createdAnimations)
1146 noteLayerPropertyChanged(AnimationChanged | CoverageRectChanged);
1147
1148 return createdAnimations;
1149}

1151void GraphicsLayerCA::pauseAnimation(const String& animationName, double timeOffset)
1152{
1153 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << "GraphicsLayerCA " << this << " id " << primaryLayerID() << " pauseAnimation " << animationName << " (is running " << animationIsRunning(animationName) << ")");
1154
1155 for (auto& animation : m_animations) {
1156 // There may be several animations with the same name in the case of transform animations
1157 // animating multiple components as individual animations.
1158 if (animation.m_name == animationName && !animation.m_pendingRemoval) {
1159 animation.m_playState = PlayState::PausePending;
1160 animation.m_timeOffset = Seconds { timeOffset };
1161
1162 noteLayerPropertyChanged(AnimationChanged);
1163 }
1164 }
1165}

1167void GraphicsLayerCA::removeAnimation(const String& animationName)
1168{
1169 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Animations, stream << "GraphicsLayerCA " << this << " id " << primaryLayerID() << " removeAnimation " << animationName << " (is running " << animationIsRunning(animationName) << ")");

1310void GraphicsLayerCA::setContentsToPlatformLayer(PlatformLayer* platformLayer, ContentsLayerPurpose purpose)
1311{
1312 if (m_contentsLayer && platformLayer == m_contentsLayer->platformLayer())
1313 return;
1314
1315 // FIXME: The passed in layer might be a raw layer or an externally created
1316 // PlatformCALayer. To determine this we attempt to get the
1317 // PlatformCALayer pointer. If this returns a null pointer we assume it's
1318 // raw. This test might be invalid if the raw layer is, for instance, the
1319 // PlatformCALayer is using a user data pointer in the raw layer, and
1320 // the creator of the raw layer is using it for some other purpose.
1321 // For now we don't support such a case.
1322 if (platformLayer) {
1323 auto platformCALayer = PlatformCALayer::platformCALayerForLayer(platformLayer);
1324 if (platformCALayer)
1325 m_contentsLayer = WTFMove(platformCALayer);
1326 else
1327 m_contentsLayer = createPlatformCALayer(platformLayer, this);
1328 } else
1329 m_contentsLayer = nullptr;
1330
1331 m_contentsLayerPurpose = platformLayer ? purpose : ContentsLayerPurpose::None;
1332
1333 noteSublayersChanged();
1334 noteLayerPropertyChanged(ContentsPlatformLayerChanged);
1335}

1362FloatPoint GraphicsLayerCA::computePositionRelativeToBase(float& pageScale) const
1363{
1364 pageScale = 1;
1365
1366 FloatPoint offset;
1367 for (const GraphicsLayer* currLayer = this; currLayer; currLayer = currLayer->parent()) {
1368 if (currLayer->appliesPageScale()) {
1369 pageScale = currLayer->pageScaleFactor();
1370 return offset;
1371 }
1372
1373 offset += currLayer->position();
1374 }
1375
1376 return FloatPoint();
1377}

1379void GraphicsLayerCA::flushCompositingState(const FloatRect& visibleRect)
1380{
1381 TransformState state(TransformState::UnapplyInverseTransformDirection, FloatQuad(visibleRect));
1382 state.setSecondaryQuad(FloatQuad { visibleRect });
1383
1384 CommitState commitState;
1385 commitState.ancestorHadChanges = visibleRect != m_previousCommittedVisibleRect;
1386 m_previousCommittedVisibleRect = visibleRect;
1387
1388#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1389 // In WK1, UIKit may be changing layer bounds behind our back in overflow-scroll layers, so disable the optimization.
1390 // See the similar test in computeVisibleAndCoverageRect().
1391 if (m_layer->isPlatformCALayerCocoa())
1392 commitState.ancestorHadChanges = true;
1393#endif
1394
1395 recursiveCommitChanges(commitState, state);
1396}
1397
1398void GraphicsLayerCA::flushCompositingStateForThisLayerOnly()
1399{
1400 float pageScaleFactor;
1401 bool layerTypeChanged = false;
1402
1403 CommitState commitState;
1404
1405 FloatPoint offset = computePositionRelativeToBase(pageScaleFactor);
1406 commitLayerChangesBeforeSublayers(commitState, pageScaleFactor, offset, layerTypeChanged);
1407 commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers(commitState);
1408
1409 if (layerTypeChanged)
1410 client().didChangePlatformLayerForLayer(this);
1411}
1412
1413static inline bool accumulatesTransform(const GraphicsLayerCA& layer)
1414{
1415 return !layer.masksToBounds() && (layer.preserves3D() || (layer.parent() && layer.parent()->preserves3D()));
1416}
1417
1418bool GraphicsLayerCA::recursiveVisibleRectChangeRequiresFlush(const CommitState& commitState, const TransformState& state) const
1419{
1420 TransformState localState = state;
1421 CommitState childCommitState = commitState;
1422
1423 // This may be called at times when layout has not been updated, so we want to avoid calling out to the client
1424 // for animating transforms.
1425 VisibleAndCoverageRects rects = computeVisibleAndCoverageRect(localState, accumulatesTransform(*this), 0);
1426
1427 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Layers, stream << "GraphicsLayerCA " << this << " id " << primaryLayerID() << " recursiveVisibleRectChangeRequiresFlush: visible rect " << rects.visibleRect << " coverage rect " << rects.coverageRect);
1428
1429 adjustCoverageRect(rects, m_visibleRect);
1430
1431 auto bounds = FloatRect(m_boundsOrigin, size());
1432
1433 bool intersectsCoverageRect = rects.coverageRect.intersects(bounds);
1434 if (intersectsCoverageRect != m_intersectsCoverageRect)
1435 return true;
1436
1437 if (rects.coverageRect != m_coverageRect) {
1438 if (TiledBacking* tiledBacking = this->tiledBacking()) {
1439 if (tiledBacking->tilesWouldChangeForCoverageRect(rects.coverageRect))
1440 return true;
1441 }
1442 }
1443
1444 if (m_maskLayer) {
1445 auto& maskLayerCA = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*m_maskLayer);
1446 if (maskLayerCA.recursiveVisibleRectChangeRequiresFlush(childCommitState, localState))
1447 return true;
1448 }
1449
1450 for (const auto& layer : children()) {
1451 const auto& currentChild = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(layer.get());
1452 if (currentChild.recursiveVisibleRectChangeRequiresFlush(childCommitState, localState))
1453 return true;
1454 }
1455
1456 if (m_replicaLayer)
1457 if (downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*m_replicaLayer).recursiveVisibleRectChangeRequiresFlush(childCommitState, localState))
1458 return true;
1459
1460 return false;
1461}
1462
1463bool GraphicsLayerCA::visibleRectChangeRequiresFlush(const FloatRect& clipRect) const
1464{
1465 TransformState state(TransformState::UnapplyInverseTransformDirection, FloatQuad(clipRect));
1466 CommitState commitState;
1467 return recursiveVisibleRectChangeRequiresFlush(commitState, state);
1468}
1469
1470TiledBacking* GraphicsLayerCA::tiledBacking() const
1471{
1472 return m_layer->tiledBacking();
1473}
1474
1475TransformationMatrix GraphicsLayerCA::layerTransform(const FloatPoint& position, const TransformationMatrix* customTransform) const
1476{
1477 TransformationMatrix transform;
1478 transform.translate(position.x(), position.y());
1479
1480 TransformationMatrix currentTransform;
1481 if (customTransform)
1482 currentTransform = *customTransform;
1483 else if (m_transform)
1484 currentTransform = *m_transform;
1485
1486 transform.multiply(transformByApplyingAnchorPoint(currentTransform));
1487
1488 if (GraphicsLayer* parentLayer = parent()) {
1489 if (parentLayer->hasNonIdentityChildrenTransform()) {
1490 FloatPoint boundsOrigin = parentLayer->boundsOrigin();
1491
1492 FloatPoint3D parentAnchorPoint(parentLayer->anchorPoint());
1493 parentAnchorPoint.scale(parentLayer->size().width(), parentLayer->size().height(), 1);
1494 parentAnchorPoint += boundsOrigin;
1495
1496 transform.translateRight3d(-parentAnchorPoint.x(), -parentAnchorPoint.y(), -parentAnchorPoint.z());
1497 transform = parentLayer->childrenTransform() * transform;
1498 transform.translateRight3d(parentAnchorPoint.x(), parentAnchorPoint.y(), parentAnchorPoint.z());
1499 }
1500 }
1501
1502 return transform;
1503}
1504
1505TransformationMatrix GraphicsLayerCA::transformByApplyingAnchorPoint(const TransformationMatrix& matrix) const
1506{
1507 if (matrix.isIdentity())
1508 return matrix;
1509
1510 TransformationMatrix result;
1511 FloatPoint3D absoluteAnchorPoint(anchorPoint());
1512 absoluteAnchorPoint.scale(size().width(), size().height(), 1);
1513 result.translate3d(absoluteAnchorPoint.x(), absoluteAnchorPoint.y(), absoluteAnchorPoint.z());
1514 result.multiply(matrix);
1515 result.translate3d(-absoluteAnchorPoint.x(), -absoluteAnchorPoint.y(), -absoluteAnchorPoint.z());
1516 return result;
1517}
1518
1519GraphicsLayerCA::VisibleAndCoverageRects GraphicsLayerCA::computeVisibleAndCoverageRect(TransformState& state, bool preserves3D, ComputeVisibleRectFlags flags) const
1520{
1521 FloatPoint position = approximatePosition();
1522 client().customPositionForVisibleRectComputation(this, position);
1523
1524 TransformationMatrix layerTransform;
1525 TransformationMatrix currentTransform;
1526 if ((flags & RespectAnimatingTransforms) && client().getCurrentTransform(this, currentTransform))
1527 layerTransform = this->layerTransform(position, &currentTransform);
1528 else
1529 layerTransform = this->layerTransform(position);
1530
1531 bool applyWasClamped;
1532 TransformState::TransformAccumulation accumulation = preserves3D ? TransformState::AccumulateTransform : TransformState::FlattenTransform;
1533 state.applyTransform(layerTransform, accumulation, &applyWasClamped);
1534
1535 bool mapWasClamped;
1536 FloatRect clipRectForChildren = state.mappedQuad(&mapWasClamped).boundingBox();
1537 FloatPoint boundsOrigin = m_boundsOrigin;
1538#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1539 // In WK1, UIKit may be changing layer bounds behind our back in overflow-scroll layers, so use the layer's origin.
1540 if (m_layer->isPlatformCALayerCocoa())
1541 boundsOrigin = m_layer->bounds().location();
1542#endif
1543 clipRectForChildren.move(boundsOrigin.x(), boundsOrigin.y());
1544
1545 FloatRect clipRectForSelf(boundsOrigin, m_size);
1546 if (!applyWasClamped && !mapWasClamped)
1547 clipRectForSelf.intersect(clipRectForChildren);
1548
1549 if (masksToBounds()) {
1550 ASSERT(accumulation == TransformState::FlattenTransform);
1551 // Flatten, and replace the quad in the TransformState with one that is clipped to this layer's bounds.
1552 state.flatten();
1553 state.setQuad(clipRectForSelf);
1554 if (state.isMappingSecondaryQuad())
1555 state.setSecondaryQuad(FloatQuad { clipRectForSelf });
1556 }
1557
1558 FloatRect coverageRect = clipRectForSelf;
1559 auto quad = state.mappedSecondaryQuad(&mapWasClamped);
1560 if (quad && !mapWasClamped && !applyWasClamped)
1561 coverageRect = (*quad).boundingBox();
1562
1563 return { clipRectForSelf, coverageRect, currentTransform };
1564}
1565
1566bool GraphicsLayerCA::adjustCoverageRect(VisibleAndCoverageRects& rects, const FloatRect& oldVisibleRect) const
1567{
1568 FloatRect coverageRect = rects.coverageRect;
1569
1570 switch (type()) {
1571 case Type::PageTiledBacking:
1572 coverageRect = tiledBacking()->adjustTileCoverageRectForScrolling(coverageRect, size(), oldVisibleRect, rects.visibleRect, pageScaleFactor() * deviceScaleFactor());
1573 break;
1574 case Type::ScrolledContents:
1575 if (m_layer->usesTiledBackingLayer())
1576 coverageRect = tiledBacking()->adjustTileCoverageRectForScrolling(coverageRect, size(), oldVisibleRect, rects.visibleRect, pageScaleFactor() * deviceScaleFactor());
1577 else {
1578 // Even if we don't have tiled backing, we want to expand coverage so that contained layers get attached backing store.
1579 coverageRect = adjustCoverageRectForMovement(coverageRect, oldVisibleRect, rects.visibleRect);
1580 }
1581 break;
1582 case Type::Normal:
1583 if (m_layer->usesTiledBackingLayer())
1584 coverageRect = tiledBacking()->adjustTileCoverageRect(coverageRect, oldVisibleRect, rects.visibleRect, size() != m_sizeAtLastCoverageRectUpdate);
1585 break;
1586 default:
1587 break;
1588 }
1589
1590 if (rects.coverageRect == coverageRect)
1591 return false;
1592
1593 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Layers, stream << "GraphicsLayerCA " << this << " id " << primaryLayerID() << " adjustCoverageRect: coverage rect adjusted from " << rects.coverageRect << " to " << coverageRect);
1594
1595 rects.coverageRect = coverageRect;
1596 return true;
1597}
1598
1599void GraphicsLayerCA::setVisibleAndCoverageRects(const VisibleAndCoverageRects& rects)
1600{
1601 bool visibleRectChanged = rects.visibleRect != m_visibleRect;
1602 bool coverageRectChanged = rects.coverageRect != m_coverageRect;
1603 if (!visibleRectChanged && !coverageRectChanged && !animationExtent())
1604 return;
1605
1606 auto bounds = FloatRect(m_boundsOrigin, size());
1607 if (auto extent = animationExtent()) {
1608 // Adjust the animation extent to match the current animation position.
1609 auto animatingTransformWithAnchorPoint = transformByApplyingAnchorPoint(rects.animatingTransform);
1610 bounds = animatingTransformWithAnchorPoint.inverse().value_or(TransformationMatrix()).mapRect(*extent);
1611 }
1612
1613 // FIXME: we need to take reflections into account when determining whether this layer intersects the coverage rect.
1614 bool intersectsCoverageRect = rects.coverageRect.intersects(bounds);
1615
1616 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Layers, stream << "GraphicsLayerCA " << this << " id " << primaryLayerID() << " setVisibleAndCoverageRects: coverage rect " << rects.coverageRect << " intersects bounds " << bounds << " " << intersectsCoverageRect);
1617
1618 if (intersectsCoverageRect != m_intersectsCoverageRect) {
1619 addUncommittedChanges(CoverageRectChanged);
1620 m_intersectsCoverageRect = intersectsCoverageRect;
1621 }
1622
1623 if (visibleRectChanged) {
1624 addUncommittedChanges(CoverageRectChanged);
1625 m_visibleRect = rects.visibleRect;
1626 }
1627
1628 if (coverageRectChanged) {
1629 addUncommittedChanges(CoverageRectChanged);
1630 m_coverageRect = rects.coverageRect;
1631 }
1632}
1633
1634bool GraphicsLayerCA::needsCommit(const CommitState& commitState)
1635{
1636 if (commitState.ancestorHadChanges)
1637 return true;
1638 if (m_uncommittedChanges)
1639 return true;
1640 if (hasDescendantsWithUncommittedChanges())
1641 return true;
1642 // Accelerated transforms move the underlying layers without GraphicsLayers getting invalidated.
1643 if (isRunningTransformAnimation())
1644 return true;
1645 if (hasDescendantsWithRunningTransformAnimations())
1646 return true;
1647
1648 return false;
1649}
1650
1651// rootRelativeTransformForScaling is a transform from the root, but for layers with transform animations, it cherry-picked the state of the
1652// animation that contributes maximally to the scale (on every layer with animations down the hierarchy).
1653void GraphicsLayerCA::recursiveCommitChanges(CommitState& commitState, const TransformState& state, float pageScaleFactor, const FloatPoint& positionRelativeToBase, bool affectedByPageScale)
1654{
1655 if (!needsCommit(commitState))
1656 return;
1657
1658 TransformState localState = state;
1659 CommitState childCommitState = commitState;
1660
1661 bool affectedByTransformAnimation = commitState.ancestorHasTransformAnimation;
1662
1663 bool accumulateTransform = accumulatesTransform(*this);
1664 VisibleAndCoverageRects rects = computeVisibleAndCoverageRect(localState, accumulateTransform);
1665 if (adjustCoverageRect(rects, m_visibleRect)) {
1666 if (state.isMappingSecondaryQuad())
1667 localState.setLastPlanarSecondaryQuad(FloatQuad { rects.coverageRect });
1668 }
1669 setVisibleAndCoverageRects(rects);
1670
1671 if (commitState.ancestorStartedOrEndedTransformAnimation)
1672 addUncommittedChanges(CoverageRectChanged);
1673
1674#ifdef VISIBLE_TILE_WASH
1675 // Use having a transform as a key to making the tile wash layer. If every layer gets a wash,
1676 // they start to obscure useful information.
1677 if ((!m_transform.isIdentity() || tiledBacking()) && !m_visibleTileWashLayer) {
1678 constexpr auto washFillColor = Color::red.colorWithAlphaByte(50);
1679 constexpr auto washBorderColor = Color::red.colorWithAlphaByte(100);
1680
1681 m_visibleTileWashLayer = createPlatformCALayer(PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeLayer, this);
1682 m_visibleTileWashLayer->setName(makeString("Visible Tile Wash Layer 0x", hex(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(m_visibleTileWashLayer->platformLayer()), Lowercase)));
1683 m_visibleTileWashLayer->setAnchorPoint(FloatPoint3D(0, 0, 0));
1684 m_visibleTileWashLayer->setBorderColor(washBorderColor);
1685 m_visibleTileWashLayer->setBorderWidth(8);
1686 m_visibleTileWashLayer->setBackgroundColor(washFillColor);
1687 noteSublayersChanged(DontScheduleFlush);
1688 }
1689
1690 if (m_visibleTileWashLayer) {
1691 m_visibleTileWashLayer->setPosition(m_visibleRect.location());
1692 m_visibleTileWashLayer->setBounds(FloatRect(FloatPoint(), m_visibleRect.size()));
1693 }
1694#endif
1695
1696 bool hadChanges = m_uncommittedChanges;
1697
1698 // FIXME: This could be more fine-grained. Only some types of changes have impact on sublayers.
1699 if (!childCommitState.ancestorHadChanges)
1700 childCommitState.ancestorHadChanges = hadChanges;
1701
1702 if (appliesPageScale()) {
1703 pageScaleFactor = this->pageScaleFactor();
1704 affectedByPageScale = true;
1705 }
1706
1707 // Accumulate an offset from the ancestral pixel-aligned layer.
1708 FloatPoint baseRelativePosition = positionRelativeToBase;
1709 if (affectedByPageScale)
1710 baseRelativePosition += m_position;
1711
1712 bool wasRunningTransformAnimation = isRunningTransformAnimation();
1713 bool layerTypeChanged = false;
1714
1715 commitLayerChangesBeforeSublayers(childCommitState, pageScaleFactor, baseRelativePosition, layerTypeChanged);
1716
1717 bool nowRunningTransformAnimation = wasRunningTransformAnimation;
1718 if (m_uncommittedChanges & AnimationChanged)
1719 nowRunningTransformAnimation = isRunningTransformAnimation();
1720
1721 if (wasRunningTransformAnimation != nowRunningTransformAnimation)
1722 childCommitState.ancestorStartedOrEndedTransformAnimation = true;
1723
1724 if (nowRunningTransformAnimation) {
1725 childCommitState.ancestorHasTransformAnimation = true;
1726 if (m_intersectsCoverageRect || !animationExtent())
1727 childCommitState.ancestorWithTransformAnimationIntersectsCoverageRect = true;
1728 affectedByTransformAnimation = true;
1729 }
1730
1731 if (GraphicsLayerCA* maskLayer = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(m_maskLayer.get())) {
1732 maskLayer->setVisibleAndCoverageRects(rects);
1733 maskLayer->commitLayerChangesBeforeSublayers(childCommitState, pageScaleFactor, baseRelativePosition, layerTypeChanged);
1734 }
1735
1736 bool hasDescendantsWithRunningTransformAnimations = false;
1737
1738 for (auto& layer : children()) {
1739 auto& currentChild = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(layer.get());
1740 currentChild.recursiveCommitChanges(childCommitState, localState, pageScaleFactor, baseRelativePosition, affectedByPageScale);
1741
1742 if (currentChild.isRunningTransformAnimation() || currentChild.hasDescendantsWithRunningTransformAnimations())
1743 hasDescendantsWithRunningTransformAnimations = true;
1744 }
1745
1746 commitState.totalBackdropFilterArea = childCommitState.totalBackdropFilterArea;
1747
1748 if (GraphicsLayerCA* replicaLayer = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(m_replicaLayer.get()))
1749 replicaLayer->recursiveCommitChanges(childCommitState, localState, pageScaleFactor, baseRelativePosition, affectedByPageScale);
1750
1751 if (GraphicsLayerCA* maskLayer = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(m_maskLayer.get()))
1752 maskLayer->commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers(childCommitState);
1753
1754 setHasDescendantsWithUncommittedChanges(false);
1755 setHasDescendantsWithRunningTransformAnimations(hasDescendantsWithRunningTransformAnimations);
1756
1757 bool hadDirtyRects = m_uncommittedChanges & DirtyRectsChanged;
1758 commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers(childCommitState);
1759
1760 if (affectedByTransformAnimation && m_layer->layerType() == PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeTiledBackingLayer)
1761 client().notifyFlushBeforeDisplayRefresh(this);
1762
1763 if (layerTypeChanged)
1764 client().didChangePlatformLayerForLayer(this);
1765
1766 if (usesDisplayListDrawing() && m_drawsContent && (!m_hasEverPainted || hadDirtyRects)) {
1767 TraceScope tracingScope(DisplayListRecordStart, DisplayListRecordEnd);
1768
1769 m_displayList = makeUnique<DisplayList::InMemoryDisplayList>();
1770
1771 FloatRect initialClip(boundsOrigin(), size());
1772
1773 DisplayList::Recorder context(*m_displayList, GraphicsContextState(), initialClip, AffineTransform());
1774 paintGraphicsLayerContents(context, FloatRect(FloatPoint(), size()));
1775 }
1776}

1780 noteLayerPropertyChanged(ChildrenChanged, m_isCommittingChanges ? DontScheduleFlush : ScheduleFlush);
1781}

1853{
1854 return layerType == PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeLightSystemBackdropLayer || layerType == PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeDarkSystemBackdropLayer;

1856
1857void GraphicsLayerCA::commitLayerChangesBeforeSublayers(CommitState& commitState, float pageScaleFactor, const FloatPoint& positionRelativeToBase, bool& layerChanged)
1858{
1859 SetForScope<bool> committingChangesChange(m_isCommittingChanges, true);
1860
1861 ++commitState.treeDepth;
1862 if (m_structuralLayer)
1863 ++commitState.treeDepth;
1864
1865 if (!m_uncommittedChanges) {
1866 // Ensure that we cap layer depth in commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers().
1867 if (commitState.treeDepth > cMaxLayerTreeDepth)
1868 addUncommittedChanges(ChildrenChanged);
1869 }
1870
1871 bool needTiledLayer = requiresTiledLayer(pageScaleFactor);
1872 bool needBackdropLayerType = (customAppearance() == CustomAppearance::LightBackdrop || customAppearance() == CustomAppearance::DarkBackdrop);
1873
1874 PlatformCALayer::LayerType currentLayerType = m_layer->layerType();
1875 PlatformCALayer::LayerType neededLayerType = currentLayerType;
1876
1877 if (needBackdropLayerType)
1878 neededLayerType = layerTypeForCustomBackdropAppearance(customAppearance());
1879 else if (needTiledLayer)
1880 neededLayerType = PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeTiledBackingLayer;
1881 else if (currentLayerType == PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeTiledBackingLayer || isCustomBackdropLayerType(m_layer->layerType()))
1882 neededLayerType = PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeWebLayer;
1883
1884 if (neededLayerType != m_layer->layerType()) {
1885 changeLayerTypeTo(neededLayerType);
1886 layerChanged = true;
1887 }
1888
1889 // Need to handle Preserves3DChanged first, because it affects which layers subsequent properties are applied to
1890 if (m_uncommittedChanges & (Preserves3DChanged | ReplicatedLayerChanged | BackdropFiltersChanged)) {
1891 if (updateStructuralLayer())
1892 layerChanged = true;
1893 }
1894
1895 if (m_uncommittedChanges & GeometryChanged)
1896 updateGeometry(pageScaleFactor, positionRelativeToBase);
1897
1898 if (m_uncommittedChanges & DrawsContentChanged)
1899 updateDrawsContent();
1900
1901 if (m_uncommittedChanges & NameChanged)
1902 updateNames();
1903
1904 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ContentsImageChanged) // Needs to happen before ChildrenChanged
1905 updateContentsImage();
1906
1907 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ContentsPlatformLayerChanged) // Needs to happen before ChildrenChanged
1908 updateContentsPlatformLayer();
1909
1910 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ContentsColorLayerChanged) // Needs to happen before ChildrenChanged
1911 updateContentsColorLayer();
1912
1913 if (m_uncommittedChanges & BackgroundColorChanged)
1914 updateBackgroundColor();
1915
1916 if (m_uncommittedChanges & TransformChanged)
1917 updateTransform();
1918
1919 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ChildrenTransformChanged)
1920 updateChildrenTransform();
1921
1922 if (m_uncommittedChanges & MasksToBoundsChanged)
1923 updateMasksToBounds();
1924
1925 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ContentsVisibilityChanged)
1926 updateContentsVisibility();
1927
1928 if (m_uncommittedChanges & UserInteractionEnabledChanged)
1929 updateUserInteractionEnabled();
1930
1931 // Note that contentsScale can affect whether the layer can be opaque.
1932 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ContentsOpaqueChanged)
1933 updateContentsOpaque(pageScaleFactor);
1934
1935 if (m_uncommittedChanges & BackfaceVisibilityChanged)
1936 updateBackfaceVisibility();
1937
1938 if (m_uncommittedChanges & OpacityChanged)
1939 updateOpacityOnLayer();
1940
1941 if (m_uncommittedChanges & FiltersChanged)
1942 updateFilters();
1943
1944 // If there are backdrop filters, we need to always check the resource usage
1945 // because something up the tree may have changed its usage.
1946 if (m_uncommittedChanges & BackdropFiltersChanged || needsBackdrop())
1947 updateBackdropFilters(commitState);
1948
1949 if (m_uncommittedChanges & BackdropFiltersRectChanged)
1950 updateBackdropFiltersRect();
1951
1952#if ENABLE(CSS_COMPOSITING)
1953 if (m_uncommittedChanges & BlendModeChanged)
1954 updateBlendMode();
1955#endif
1956
1957 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ShapeChanged)
1958 updateShape();
1959
1960 if (m_uncommittedChanges & WindRuleChanged)
1961 updateWindRule();
1962
1963 if (m_uncommittedChanges & AnimationChanged)
1964 updateAnimations();
1965
1966 // Updating the contents scale can cause parts of the layer to be invalidated,
1967 // so make sure to update the contents scale before updating the dirty rects.
1968 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ContentsScaleChanged)
1969 updateContentsScale(pageScaleFactor);
1970
1971 if (m_uncommittedChanges & CoverageRectChanged)
1972 updateCoverage(commitState);
1973
1974 if (m_uncommittedChanges & AcceleratesDrawingChanged) // Needs to happen before TilingAreaChanged.
1975 updateAcceleratesDrawing();
1976
1977 if (m_uncommittedChanges & TilingAreaChanged) // Needs to happen after CoverageRectChanged, ContentsScaleChanged
1978 updateTiles();
1979
1980 if (m_uncommittedChanges & DirtyRectsChanged)
1981 repaintLayerDirtyRects();
1982
1983 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ContentsRectsChanged) // Needs to happen before ChildrenChanged
1984 updateContentsRects();
1985
1986 if (m_uncommittedChanges & MasksToBoundsRectChanged) // Needs to happen before ChildrenChanged
1987 updateMasksToBoundsRect();
1988
1989 if (m_uncommittedChanges & EventRegionChanged)
1990 updateEventRegion();
1991
1992#if ENABLE(SCROLLING_THREAD)
1993 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ScrollingNodeChanged)
1994 updateScrollingNode();
1995#endif
1996
1997 if (m_uncommittedChanges & MaskLayerChanged) {
1998 updateMaskLayer();
1999 // If the mask layer becomes tiled it can set this flag again. Clear the flag so that
2000 // commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers doesn't update the mask again in the normal case.
2001 m_uncommittedChanges &= ~MaskLayerChanged;
2002 }
2003
2004 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ContentsNeedsDisplay)
2005 updateContentsNeedsDisplay();
2006
2007 if (m_uncommittedChanges & SupportsSubpixelAntialiasedTextChanged)
2008 updateSupportsSubpixelAntialiasedText();
2009
2010 if (m_uncommittedChanges & DebugIndicatorsChanged)
2011 updateDebugIndicators();
2012
2013 if (m_uncommittedChanges & CustomAppearanceChanged)
2014 updateCustomAppearance();
2015
2016#if HAVE(CORE_ANIMATION_SEPARATED_LAYERS)
2017 if (m_uncommittedChanges & SeparatedChanged)
2018 updateIsSeparated();
2019
2020#if HAVE(CORE_ANIMATION_SEPARATED_PORTALS)
2021 if (m_uncommittedChanges & SeparatedPortalChanged)
2022 updateIsSeparatedPortal();
2023
2024 if (m_uncommittedChanges & DescendentOfSeparatedPortalChanged)
2025 updateIsDescendentOfSeparatedPortal();
2026#endif
2027#endif
2028
2029 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ChildrenChanged) {
2030 updateSublayerList();
2031 // Sublayers may set this flag again, so clear it to avoid always updating sublayers in commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers().
2032 m_uncommittedChanges &= ~ChildrenChanged;
2033 }
2034
2035 // Ensure that we cap layer depth in commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers().
2036 if (commitState.treeDepth > cMaxLayerTreeDepth)
2037 addUncommittedChanges(ChildrenChanged);
2038}
2039
2040void GraphicsLayerCA::commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers(CommitState& commitState)
2041{
2042 if (!m_uncommittedChanges)
2043 return;
2044
2045 SetForScope<bool> committingChangesChange(m_isCommittingChanges, true);
2046
2047 if (m_uncommittedChanges & MaskLayerChanged)
2048 updateMaskLayer();
2049
2050 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ChildrenChanged)
2051 updateSublayerList(commitState.treeDepth > cMaxLayerTreeDepth);
2052
2053 if (m_uncommittedChanges & ReplicatedLayerChanged)
2054 updateReplicatedLayers();
2055
2056 m_uncommittedChanges = NoChange;
2057}

2059void GraphicsLayerCA::updateNames()
2060{
2061 auto name = debugName();
2062 switch (structuralLayerPurpose()) {
2063 case StructuralLayerForPreserves3D:
2064 m_structuralLayer->setName("preserve-3d: " + name);
2065 break;
2066 case StructuralLayerForReplicaFlattening:
2067 m_structuralLayer->setName("replica flattening: " + name);
2068 break;
2069 case StructuralLayerForBackdrop:
2070 m_structuralLayer->setName("backdrop hosting: " + name);
2071 break;
2072 case NoStructuralLayer:
2073 break;
2074 }
2075 m_layer->setName(name);
2076}
2077
2078void GraphicsLayerCA::updateSublayerList(bool maxLayerDepthReached)
2079{
2080 if (maxLayerDepthReached) {
2081 m_layer->setSublayers({ });
2082 return;
2083 }
2084
2085 auto appendStructuralLayerChildren = [&](PlatformCALayerList& list) {
2086 if (m_backdropLayer)
2087 list.append(m_backdropLayer);
2088
2089 if (m_replicaLayer)
2090 list.append(downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*m_replicaLayer).primaryLayer());
2091
2092 list.append(m_layer);
2093 };
2094
2095 auto appendContentsLayer = [&](PlatformCALayerList& list) {
2096 if (m_contentsVisible && m_contentsLayer)
2097 list.append(m_contentsLayer);
2098 };
2099
2100 auto appendClippingLayers = [&](PlatformCALayerList& list) {
2101 if (m_contentsVisible && m_contentsClippingLayer)
2102 list.append(m_contentsClippingLayer);
2103 };
2104
2105 auto appendCustomAndClippingLayers = [&](PlatformCALayerList& list) {
2106 if (auto* customSublayers = m_layer->customSublayers())
2107 list.appendVector(*customSublayers);
2108
2109 if (m_contentsClippingLayer)
2110 appendClippingLayers(list);
2111 else
2112 appendContentsLayer(list);
2113 };
2114
2115 auto appendLayersFromChildren = [&](PlatformCALayerList& list) {
2116 for (const auto& layer : children()) {
2117 const auto& currentChild = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(layer.get());
2118 PlatformCALayer* childLayer = currentChild.layerForSuperlayer();
2119 list.append(childLayer);
2120 }
2121 };
2122
2123 auto appendDebugLayers = [&](PlatformCALayerList& list) {
2124#ifdef VISIBLE_TILE_WASH
2125 if (m_visibleTileWashLayer)
2126 list.append(m_visibleTileWashLayer);
2127#else
2128 UNUSED_PARAM(list);
2129#endif
2130 };
2131
2132 auto buildChildLayerList = [&](PlatformCALayerList& list) {
2133 appendLayersFromChildren(list);
2134 appendDebugLayers(list);
2135 };
2136
2137 PlatformCALayerList primaryLayerChildren;
2138 appendCustomAndClippingLayers(primaryLayerChildren);
2139
2140 bool clippingLayerHostsChildren = m_contentsRectClipsDescendants && m_contentsClippingLayer;
2141 if (m_contentsClippingLayer) {
2142 PlatformCALayerList clippingChildren;
2143 if (clippingLayerHostsChildren)
2144 buildChildLayerList(clippingChildren);
2145 appendContentsLayer(clippingChildren);
2146 m_contentsClippingLayer->setSublayers(clippingChildren);
2147 }
2148
2149 if (m_structuralLayer) {
2150 PlatformCALayerList layerList;
2151 appendStructuralLayerChildren(layerList);
2152
2153 if (!clippingLayerHostsChildren)
2154 buildChildLayerList(layerList);
2155
2156 m_structuralLayer->setSublayers(layerList);
2157 } else if (!clippingLayerHostsChildren)
2158 buildChildLayerList(primaryLayerChildren);
2159
2160 m_layer->setSublayers(primaryLayerChildren);
2161}

2163void GraphicsLayerCA::updateGeometry(float pageScaleFactor, const FloatPoint& positionRelativeToBase)
2164{
2165 FloatPoint scaledPosition = m_position;
2166 FloatPoint3D scaledAnchorPoint = m_anchorPoint;
2167 FloatSize scaledSize = m_size;
2168 FloatSize pixelAlignmentOffset;
2169
2170 // FIXME: figure out if we really need to pixel align the graphics layer here.
2171 if (client().needsPixelAligment() && !WTF::isIntegral(pageScaleFactor) && m_drawsContent && !m_masksToBounds)
2172 computePixelAlignment(pageScaleFactor, positionRelativeToBase, scaledPosition, scaledAnchorPoint, pixelAlignmentOffset);
2173
2174 // Update position.
2175 // Position is offset on the layer by the layer anchor point.
2176 FloatPoint adjustedPosition(scaledPosition.x() + scaledAnchorPoint.x() * scaledSize.width(), scaledPosition.y() + scaledAnchorPoint.y() * scaledSize.height());
2177
2178 if (m_structuralLayer) {
2179 FloatPoint layerPosition(m_position.x() + m_anchorPoint.x() * m_size.width(), m_position.y() + m_anchorPoint.y() * m_size.height());
2180 FloatRect layerBounds(m_boundsOrigin, m_size);
2181
2182 m_structuralLayer->setPosition(layerPosition);
2183 m_structuralLayer->setBounds(layerBounds);
2184 m_structuralLayer->setAnchorPoint(m_anchorPoint);
2185
2186 if (m_layerClones) {
2187 for (auto& clone : m_layerClones->structuralLayerClones) {
2188 PlatformCALayer* cloneLayer = clone.value.get();
2189 FloatPoint clonePosition = layerPosition;
2190
2191 if (m_replicaLayer && isReplicatedRootClone(clone.key)) {
2192 // Maintain the special-case position for the root of a clone subtree,
2193 // which we set up in replicatedLayerRoot().
2194 clonePosition = positionForCloneRootLayer();
2195 }
2196
2197 cloneLayer->setPosition(clonePosition);
2198 cloneLayer->setBounds(layerBounds);
2199 cloneLayer->setAnchorPoint(m_anchorPoint);
2200 }
2201 }
2202
2203 // If we have a structural layer, we just use 0.5, 0.5 for the anchor point of the main layer.
2204 scaledAnchorPoint = FloatPoint(0.5f, 0.5f);
2205 adjustedPosition = FloatPoint(scaledAnchorPoint.x() * scaledSize.width() - pixelAlignmentOffset.width(), scaledAnchorPoint.y() * scaledSize.height() - pixelAlignmentOffset.height());
2206 }
2207
2208 m_pixelAlignmentOffset = pixelAlignmentOffset;
2209
2210 // Push the layer to device pixel boundary (setPosition()), but move the content back to its original position (setBounds())
2211 m_layer->setPosition(adjustedPosition);
2212 FloatRect adjustedBounds = FloatRect(FloatPoint(m_boundsOrigin - pixelAlignmentOffset), m_size);
2213 m_layer->setBounds(adjustedBounds);
2214 m_layer->setAnchorPoint(scaledAnchorPoint);
2215
2216 if (m_layerClones) {
2217 for (auto& clone : m_layerClones->primaryLayerClones) {
2218 PlatformCALayer* cloneLayer = clone.value.get();
2219 FloatPoint clonePosition = adjustedPosition;
2220
2221 if (!m_structuralLayer && m_replicaLayer && isReplicatedRootClone(clone.key)) {
2222 // Maintain the special-case position for the root of a clone subtree,
2223 // which we set up in replicatedLayerRoot().
2224 clonePosition = positionForCloneRootLayer();
2225 }
2226
2227 cloneLayer->setPosition(clonePosition);
2228 cloneLayer->setBounds(adjustedBounds);
2229 cloneLayer->setAnchorPoint(scaledAnchorPoint);
2230 }
2231 }
2232}

2350void GraphicsLayerCA::updateBackdropFilters(CommitState& commitState)
2351{
2352 bool canHaveBackdropFilters = needsBackdrop();
2353 if (canHaveBackdropFilters) {
2354 canHaveBackdropFilters = false;
2355 IntRect backdropFilterRect = enclosingIntRect(m_backdropFiltersRect.rect());
2356 if (backdropFilterRect.width() > 0 && backdropFilterRect.height() > 0) {
2357 CheckedUint32 backdropFilterArea = CheckedUint32(backdropFilterRect.width()) * CheckedUint32(backdropFilterRect.height());
2358 if (!backdropFilterArea.hasOverflowed()) {
2359 CheckedUint32 newTotalBackdropFilterArea = CheckedUint32(commitState.totalBackdropFilterArea) + backdropFilterArea;
2360 if (!newTotalBackdropFilterArea.hasOverflowed() && newTotalBackdropFilterArea <= cMaxTotalBackdropFilterArea) {
2361 commitState.totalBackdropFilterArea = newTotalBackdropFilterArea;
2362 canHaveBackdropFilters = true;
2363 }
2364 }
2365 }
2366 }
2367
2368 if (!canHaveBackdropFilters) {
2369 if (m_backdropLayer) {
2370 m_backdropLayer->removeFromSuperlayer();
2371 m_backdropLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
2372 m_backdropLayer = nullptr;
2373 }
2374 return;
2375 }
2376
2377 // If nothing actually changed, no need to touch the layer properties.
2378 if (!(m_uncommittedChanges & BackdropFiltersChanged))
2379 return;
2380
2381 bool madeLayer = !m_backdropLayer;
2382 if (!m_backdropLayer) {
2383 m_backdropLayer = createPlatformCALayer(PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeBackdropLayer, this);
2384 m_backdropLayer->setAnchorPoint(FloatPoint3D());
2385 m_backdropLayer->setMasksToBounds(true);
2386 m_backdropLayer->setName(MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("backdrop"));
2387 }
2388
2389 m_backdropLayer->setHidden(!m_contentsVisible);
2390 m_backdropLayer->setFilters(m_backdropFilters);
2391
2392 if (m_layerClones) {
2393 for (auto& clone : m_layerClones->backdropLayerClones) {
2394 PlatformCALayer* cloneLayer = clone.value.get();
2395 cloneLayer->setHidden(!m_contentsVisible);
2396 cloneLayer->setFilters(m_backdropFilters);
2397 }
2398 }
2399
2400 if (madeLayer) {
2401 updateBackdropFiltersRect();
2402 noteSublayersChanged(DontScheduleFlush);
2403 }
2404}

2406void GraphicsLayerCA::updateBackdropFiltersRect()
2407{
2408 if (!m_backdropLayer)
2409 return;
2410
2411 FloatRect contentBounds(0, 0, m_backdropFiltersRect.rect().width(), m_backdropFiltersRect.rect().height());
2412 m_backdropLayer->setBounds(contentBounds);
2413 m_backdropLayer->setPosition(m_backdropFiltersRect.rect().location());
2414
2415 auto backdropRectRelativeToBackdropLayer = m_backdropFiltersRect;
2416 backdropRectRelativeToBackdropLayer.setLocation({ });
2417 updateClippingStrategy(*m_backdropLayer, m_backdropClippingLayer, backdropRectRelativeToBackdropLayer);
2418
2419 if (m_layerClones) {
2420 for (auto& clone : m_layerClones->backdropLayerClones) {
2421 PlatformCALayer* backdropCloneLayer = clone.value.get();
2422 backdropCloneLayer->setBounds(contentBounds);
2423 backdropCloneLayer->setPosition(m_backdropFiltersRect.rect().location());
2424
2425 CloneID cloneID = clone.key;
2426 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> backdropClippingLayerClone = m_layerClones->backdropClippingLayerClones.get(cloneID);
2427
2428 bool hadBackdropClippingLayer = backdropClippingLayerClone;
2429 updateClippingStrategy(*backdropCloneLayer, backdropClippingLayerClone, backdropRectRelativeToBackdropLayer);
2430
2431 if (!backdropClippingLayerClone)
2432 m_layerClones->backdropClippingLayerClones.remove(cloneID);
2433 else if (backdropClippingLayerClone && !hadBackdropClippingLayer)
2434 m_layerClones->backdropClippingLayerClones.add(cloneID, backdropClippingLayerClone);
2435 }
2436 }

2492
2493bool GraphicsLayerCA::ensureStructuralLayer(StructuralLayerPurpose purpose)
2494{
2495 const LayerChangeFlags structuralLayerChangeFlags = NameChanged
2496 | GeometryChanged
2497 | TransformChanged
2498 | ChildrenTransformChanged
2499 | ChildrenChanged
2500 | BackfaceVisibilityChanged
2501 | FiltersChanged
2502 | BackdropFiltersChanged
2503 | MaskLayerChanged
2504 | OpacityChanged;
2505
2506 bool structuralLayerChanged = false;
2507
2508 if (purpose == NoStructuralLayer) {
2509 if (m_structuralLayer) {
2510 // Replace the transformLayer in the parent with this layer.
2511 m_layer->removeFromSuperlayer();
2512
2513 // If m_layer doesn't have a parent, it means it's the root layer and
2514 // is likely hosted by something that is not expecting to be changed
2515 ASSERT(m_structuralLayer->superlayer());
2516 m_structuralLayer->superlayer()->replaceSublayer(*m_structuralLayer, *m_layer);
2517
2518 moveAnimations(m_structuralLayer.get(), m_layer.get());
2519
2520 // Release the structural layer.
2521 m_structuralLayer = nullptr;
2522 structuralLayerChanged = true;
2523
2524 addUncommittedChanges(structuralLayerChangeFlags);
2525 }
2526 return structuralLayerChanged;
2527 }
2528
2529 if (purpose == StructuralLayerForPreserves3D) {
2530 if (m_structuralLayer && m_structuralLayer->layerType() != PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeTransformLayer)
2531 m_structuralLayer = nullptr;
2532
2533 if (!m_structuralLayer) {
2534 m_structuralLayer = createPlatformCALayer(PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeTransformLayer, this);
2535 structuralLayerChanged = true;
2536 }
2537 } else {
2538 if (m_structuralLayer && m_structuralLayer->layerType() != PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeLayer)
2539 m_structuralLayer = nullptr;
2540
2541 if (!m_structuralLayer) {
2542 m_structuralLayer = createPlatformCALayer(PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeLayer, this);
2543 structuralLayerChanged = true;
2544 }
2545 }
2546
2547 if (!structuralLayerChanged)
2548 return false;
2549
2550 addUncommittedChanges(structuralLayerChangeFlags);
2551
2552 // We've changed the layer that our parent added to its sublayer list, so tell it to update
2553 // sublayers again in its commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers().
2554 downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*parent()).noteSublayersChanged(DontScheduleFlush);
2555
2556 // Set properties of m_layer to their default values, since these are expressed on on the structural layer.
2557 FloatPoint point(m_size.width() / 2.0f, m_size.height() / 2.0f);
2558 FloatPoint3D anchorPoint(0.5f, 0.5f, 0);
2559 m_layer->setPosition(point);
2560 m_layer->setAnchorPoint(anchorPoint);
2561 m_layer->setTransform(TransformationMatrix());
2562 m_layer->setOpacity(1);
2563 if (m_layerClones) {
2564 for (auto& layer : m_layerClones->primaryLayerClones.values()) {
2565 layer->setPosition(point);
2566 layer->setAnchorPoint(anchorPoint);
2567 layer->setTransform(TransformationMatrix());
2568 layer->setOpacity(1);
2569 }
2570 }
2571
2572 moveAnimations(m_layer.get(), m_structuralLayer.get());
2573 return true;
2574}

2576GraphicsLayerCA::StructuralLayerPurpose GraphicsLayerCA::structuralLayerPurpose() const
2577{
2578 if (preserves3D())
2579 return StructuralLayerForPreserves3D;
2580
2581 if (isReplicated())
2582 return StructuralLayerForReplicaFlattening;
2583
2584 if (needsBackdrop())
2585 return StructuralLayerForBackdrop;
2586
2587 return NoStructuralLayer;

2780// The clipping strategy depends on whether the rounded rect has equal corner radii.
2781// roundedRect is in the coordinate space of clippingLayer.
2782void GraphicsLayerCA::updateClippingStrategy(PlatformCALayer& clippingLayer, RefPtr<PlatformCALayer>& shapeMaskLayer, const FloatRoundedRect& roundedRect)
2783{
2784 if (roundedRect.radii().isUniformCornerRadius() && clippingLayer.bounds() == roundedRect.rect()) {
2785 clippingLayer.setMask(nullptr);
2786 if (shapeMaskLayer) {
2787 shapeMaskLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
2788 shapeMaskLayer = nullptr;
2789 }
2790
2791 clippingLayer.setMasksToBounds(true);
2792 clippingLayer.setCornerRadius(roundedRect.radii().topLeft().width());
2793 return;
2794 }
2795
2796 if (!shapeMaskLayer) {
2797 shapeMaskLayer = createPlatformCALayer(PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeShapeLayer, this);
2798 shapeMaskLayer->setAnchorPoint({ });
2799 shapeMaskLayer->setName(MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("shape mask"));
2800 }
2801
2802 // clippingLayer's boundsOrigin is roundedRect.rect().location(), and is non-zero to positioning descendant layers.
2803 // The mask layer needs an equivalent position.
2804 auto rectLocation = roundedRect.rect().location();
2805 shapeMaskLayer->setPosition({ rectLocation.x(), rectLocation.y(), 0.0f });
2806
2807 auto shapeBounds = FloatRect { { }, roundedRect.rect().size() };
2808 shapeMaskLayer->setBounds(shapeBounds);
2809
2810 auto localRoundedRect = roundedRect;
2811 localRoundedRect.setLocation({ });
2812 shapeMaskLayer->setShapeRoundedRect(localRoundedRect);
2813
2814 clippingLayer.setCornerRadius(0);
2815 clippingLayer.setMask(shapeMaskLayer.get());
2816}

2818void GraphicsLayerCA::updateContentsRects()
2819{
2820 if (!m_contentsLayer && !m_contentsRectClipsDescendants)
2821 return;
2822
2823 auto contentBounds = FloatRect { { }, m_contentsRect.size() };
2824
2825 bool gainedOrLostClippingLayer = false;
2826 if (m_contentsClippingRect.isRounded() || !m_contentsClippingRect.rect().contains(m_contentsRect)) {
2827 if (!m_contentsClippingLayer) {
2828 m_contentsClippingLayer = createPlatformCALayer(PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeLayer, this);
2829 m_contentsClippingLayer->setAnchorPoint({ });
2830#if ENABLE(TREE_DEBUGGING)
2831 m_contentsClippingLayer->setName(makeString("contents clipping ", m_contentsClippingLayer->layerID()));
2832#else
2833 m_contentsClippingLayer->setName(MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("contents clipping"));
2834#endif
2835 gainedOrLostClippingLayer = true;
2836 }
2837
2838 m_contentsClippingLayer->setPosition(m_contentsClippingRect.rect().location());
2839 m_contentsClippingLayer->setBounds(m_contentsClippingRect.rect());
2840
2841 updateClippingStrategy(*m_contentsClippingLayer, m_contentsShapeMaskLayer, m_contentsClippingRect);
2842
2843 if (m_contentsLayer && gainedOrLostClippingLayer) {
2844 m_contentsLayer->removeFromSuperlayer();
2845 m_contentsClippingLayer->appendSublayer(*m_contentsLayer);
2846 }
2847 } else {
2848 if (m_contentsClippingLayer) {
2849 if (m_contentsLayer)
2850 m_contentsLayer->removeFromSuperlayer();
2851
2852 m_contentsClippingLayer->removeFromSuperlayer();
2853 m_contentsClippingLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
2854 m_contentsClippingLayer->setMask(nullptr);
2855 m_contentsClippingLayer = nullptr;
2856 gainedOrLostClippingLayer = true;
2857 }
2858
2859 if (m_contentsShapeMaskLayer) {
2860 m_contentsShapeMaskLayer->setOwner(nullptr);
2861 m_contentsShapeMaskLayer = nullptr;
2862 }
2863 }
2864
2865 if (gainedOrLostClippingLayer)
2866 noteSublayersChanged(DontScheduleFlush);
2867
2868 if (m_contentsLayer) {
2869 m_contentsLayer->setPosition(m_contentsRect.location());
2870 m_contentsLayer->setBounds(contentBounds);
2871 }
2872
2873 if (m_layerClones) {
2874 for (auto& layer : m_layerClones->contentsLayerClones.values()) {
2875 layer->setPosition(m_contentsRect.location());
2876 layer->setBounds(contentBounds);
2877 }
2878
2879 for (auto& clone : m_layerClones->contentsClippingLayerClones) {
2880 CloneID cloneID = clone.key;
2881 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> shapeMaskLayerClone = m_layerClones->contentsShapeMaskLayerClones.get(cloneID);
2882
2883 bool hadShapeMask = shapeMaskLayerClone;
2884 updateClippingStrategy(*clone.value, shapeMaskLayerClone, m_contentsClippingRect);
2885
2886 if (!shapeMaskLayerClone)
2887 m_layerClones->contentsShapeMaskLayerClones.remove(cloneID);
2888 else if (shapeMaskLayerClone && !hadShapeMask)
2889 m_layerClones->contentsShapeMaskLayerClones.add(cloneID, shapeMaskLayerClone);
2890 }
2891 }
2892}

2962
2963// For now, this assumes that layers only ever have one replica, so replicaIndices contains only 0 and 1.
2964GraphicsLayerCA::CloneID GraphicsLayerCA::ReplicaState::cloneID() const
2965{
2966 size_t depth = m_replicaBranches.size();
2967
2968 const size_t bitsPerUChar = sizeof(UChar) * 8;
2969 size_t vectorSize = (depth + bitsPerUChar - 1) / bitsPerUChar;
2970
2971 Vector<UChar> result(vectorSize);
2972 result.fill(0);
2973
2974 // Create a string from the bit sequence which we can use to identify the clone.
2975 // Note that the string may contain embedded nulls, but that's OK.
2976 for (size_t i = 0; i < depth; ++i) {
2977 UChar& currChar = result[i / bitsPerUChar];
2978 currChar = (currChar << 1) | m_replicaBranches[i];
2979 }
2980
2981 return String::adopt(WTFMove(result));
2982}

2984RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> GraphicsLayerCA::replicatedLayerRoot(ReplicaState& replicaState)
2985{
2986 // Limit replica nesting, to avoid 2^N explosion of replica layers.
2987 if (!m_replicatedLayer || replicaState.replicaDepth() == ReplicaState::maxReplicaDepth)
2988 return nullptr;
2989
2990 GraphicsLayerCA& replicatedLayer = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*m_replicatedLayer);
2991
2992 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> clonedLayerRoot = replicatedLayer.fetchCloneLayers(this, replicaState, RootCloneLevel);
2993 FloatPoint cloneRootPosition = replicatedLayer.positionForCloneRootLayer();
2994
2995 // Replica root has no offset or transform
2996 clonedLayerRoot->setPosition(cloneRootPosition);
2997 clonedLayerRoot->setTransform(TransformationMatrix());
2998
2999 return clonedLayerRoot;
3000}
3001
3002void GraphicsLayerCA::updateAnimations()
3003{
3004 // In order to guarantee that transform animations are applied in the expected order (translate, rotate, scale and transform),
3005 // we need to have them wrapped individually in an animation group because Core Animation sorts animations first by their begin
3006 // time, and then by the order in which they were added (for those with the same begin time). Since a rotate animation can have
3007 // an earlier begin time than a translate animation, we cannot rely on adding the animations in the correct order.
3008 //
3009 // Having an animation group wrapping each animation means that we can guarantee the order in which animations are applied by
3010 // ensuring they each have the same begin time. We set this begin time to be the smallest value possible, ensuring that base
3011 // transform animations are applied continuously. We'll then set the begin time of interpolating animations to be local to the
3012 // animation group, which means subtracting the group's begin time.
3013
3014 // We use 1_s here because 0_s would have special meaning in Core Animation, meaning that the animation would have its begin
3015 // time set to the current time when it's committed.
3016 auto animationGroupBeginTime = 1_s;
3017 auto infiniteDuration = std::numeric_limits<double>::max();
3018 auto currentTime = Seconds(CACurrentMediaTime());
3019
3020 auto addAnimationGroup = [&](AnimatedPropertyID property, const Vector<RefPtr<PlatformCAAnimation>>& animations) {
3021 auto caAnimationGroup = createPlatformCAAnimation(PlatformCAAnimation::Group, "");
3022 caAnimationGroup->setDuration(infiniteDuration);
3023 caAnimationGroup->setAnimations(animations);
3024
3025 auto animationGroup = LayerPropertyAnimation(WTFMove(caAnimationGroup), "group-" + createCanonicalUUIDString(), property, 0, 0, 0_s);
3026 animationGroup.m_beginTime = animationGroupBeginTime;
3027
3028 setAnimationOnLayer(animationGroup);
3029 m_animationGroups.append(WTFMove(animationGroup));
3030 };
3031
3032 enum class Additive { Yes, No };
3033 auto prepareAnimationForAddition = [&](LayerPropertyAnimation& animation, Additive additive = Additive::Yes) {
3034 auto caAnim = animation.m_animation;
3035 caAnim->setAdditive(additive == Additive::Yes);
3036 if (auto beginTime = animation.computedBeginTime())
3037 caAnim->setBeginTime(beginTime->seconds());
3038
3039 if (animation.m_playState == PlayState::PausePending || animation.m_playState == PlayState::Paused) {
3040 caAnim->setSpeed(0);
3041 caAnim->setTimeOffset(animation.m_timeOffset.seconds());
3042 animation.m_playState = PlayState::Paused;
3043 } else
3044 animation.m_playState = PlayState::Playing;
3045 };
3046
3047 auto addAnimation = [&](LayerPropertyAnimation& animation, Additive additive = Additive::Yes) {
3048 prepareAnimationForAddition(animation, additive);
3049 addAnimationGroup(animation.m_property, { animation.m_animation });
3050 };
3051
3052 enum class TransformationMatrixSource { UseIdentityMatrix, AskClient };
3053 auto makeBaseValueTransformAnimation = [&](AnimatedPropertyID property, TransformationMatrixSource matrixSource = TransformationMatrixSource::AskClient, Seconds beginTimeOfEarliestPropertyAnimation = 0_s) -> LayerPropertyAnimation* {
3054 // A base value transform animation can either be set to the identity matrix or to read the underlying
3055 // value from the GraphicsLayerClient. If we didn't explicitly ask for an identity matrix, we can skip
3056 // the addition of this base value transform animation since it will be a no-op.
3057 auto matrix = matrixSource == TransformationMatrixSource::UseIdentityMatrix ? TransformationMatrix() : client().transformMatrixForProperty(property);
3058 if (matrixSource == TransformationMatrixSource::AskClient && matrix.isIdentity())
3059 return nullptr;
3060
3061 auto delay = beginTimeOfEarliestPropertyAnimation > currentTime ? beginTimeOfEarliestPropertyAnimation - currentTime : 0_s;
3062
3063 // A base value transform animation needs to last forever and use the same value for its from and to values,
3064 // unless we're just filling until an animation for this property starts, in which case it must last for duration
3065 // of the delay until that animation.
3066 auto caAnimation = createPlatformCAAnimation(PlatformCAAnimation::Basic, propertyIdToString(property));
3067 caAnimation->setDuration(delay ? delay.seconds() : infiniteDuration);
3068 caAnimation->setFromValue(matrix);
3069 caAnimation->setToValue(matrix);
3070
3071 auto animation = LayerPropertyAnimation(WTFMove(caAnimation), "base-transform-" + createCanonicalUUIDString(), property, 0, 0, 0_s);
3072 if (delay)
3073 animation.m_beginTime = currentTime - animationGroupBeginTime;
3074
3075 m_baseValueTransformAnimations.append(WTFMove(animation));
3076 return &m_baseValueTransformAnimations.last();
3077 };
3078
3079 auto addBaseValueTransformAnimation = [&](AnimatedPropertyID property, TransformationMatrixSource matrixSource = TransformationMatrixSource::AskClient, Seconds beginTimeOfEarliestPropertyAnimation = 0_s) {
3080 // Additivity will depend on the source of the matrix, if it was explicitly provided as an identity matrix, it
3081 // is the initial base value transform animation and must override the current transform value for this layer.
3082 // Otherwise, it is meant to apply the underlying value for one specific transform-related property and be additive
3083 // to be combined with the other base value transform animations and interpolating animations.
3084 if (auto* animation = makeBaseValueTransformAnimation(property, matrixSource, beginTimeOfEarliestPropertyAnimation))
3085 addAnimation(*animation, matrixSource == TransformationMatrixSource::AskClient ? Additive::Yes : Additive::No);
3086 };
3087
3088 // Iterate through all animations to set the begin time of any new animations.
3089 for (auto& animation : m_animations) {
3090 if (!animation.m_pendingRemoval && !animation.m_beginTime)
3091 animation.m_beginTime = currentTime - animationGroupBeginTime;
3092 }
3093
3094 // Now, remove all animation groups from the layer so that we no longer have any layer animations.
3095 for (auto& animationGroup : m_animationGroups)
3096 removeCAAnimationFromLayer(animationGroup);
3097
3098 // We can remove all previously-created base value transform animations and animation groups.
3099 m_baseValueTransformAnimations.clear();
3100 m_animationGroups.clear();
3101
3102 // Now remove all the animations marked as pending removal.
3103 m_animations.removeAllMatching([&](LayerPropertyAnimation animation) {
3104 return animation.m_pendingRemoval;
3105 });
3106
3107 // Now that our list of animations is current, we can separate animations by property so that
3108 // we can apply them in order. We only need to apply the last animation applied for a given
3109 // individual transform property, so we keep a reference to that. For animations targeting
3110 // the transform property itself, we keep them in order since they all need to apply and build
3111 // on top of each other. Finally, animations that are not transform-related can be applied
3112 // right away since their order relative to transform animations does not matter.
3113 LayerPropertyAnimation* translateAnimation = nullptr;
3114 LayerPropertyAnimation* scaleAnimation = nullptr;
3115 LayerPropertyAnimation* rotateAnimation = nullptr;
3116 Vector<LayerPropertyAnimation*> translateAnimations;
3117 Vector<LayerPropertyAnimation*> scaleAnimations;
3118 Vector<LayerPropertyAnimation*> rotateAnimations;
3119 Vector<LayerPropertyAnimation*> transformAnimations;
3120
3121 for (auto& animation : m_animations) {
3122 switch (animation.m_property) {
3123 case AnimatedPropertyTranslate:
3124 translateAnimation = &animation;
3125 break;
3126 case AnimatedPropertyScale:
3127 scaleAnimation = &animation;
3128 break;
3129 case AnimatedPropertyRotate:
3130 rotateAnimation = &animation;
3131 break;
3132 case AnimatedPropertyTransform:
3133 // In the case of animations targeting the "transform" CSS property, there may be several
3134 // animations created for a single KeyframeEffect, one for each transform component. In that
3135 // case the animation index starts at 0 and increases for each component. If we encounter an
3136 // index of 0 this means this animation establishes a new group of animation belonging to a
3137 // single KeyframeEffect. As such, since the top-most KeyframeEffect replaces the previous
3138 // ones, we can remove all the previously-added "transform" animations.
3139 if (!animation.m_index)
3140 transformAnimations.clear();
3141 transformAnimations.append(&animation);
3142 break;
3143 case AnimatedPropertyOpacity:
3144 case AnimatedPropertyBackgroundColor:
3145 case AnimatedPropertyFilter:
3146#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
3147 case AnimatedPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter:
3148#endif
3149 addAnimation(animation, Additive::No);
3150 break;
3151 case AnimatedPropertyInvalid:
3152 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3153 }
3154 }
3155
3156 if (translateAnimation)
3157 translateAnimations.append(translateAnimation);
3158 if (scaleAnimation)
3159 scaleAnimations.append(scaleAnimation);
3160 if (rotateAnimation)
3161 rotateAnimations.append(rotateAnimation);
3162
3163 // Now we can apply the transform-related animations, taking care to add them in the right order
3164 // (translate/scale/rotate/transform) and generate non-interpolating base value transform animations
3165 // for each property that is not otherwise interpolated.
3166 if (!translateAnimations.isEmpty() || !scaleAnimations.isEmpty() || !rotateAnimations.isEmpty() || !transformAnimations.isEmpty()) {
3167 // Start with a base identity transform to override the transform applied to the layer and have a
3168 // sound base to add animations on top of with additivity enabled.
3169 addBaseValueTransformAnimation(AnimatedPropertyTransform, TransformationMatrixSource::UseIdentityMatrix);
3170
3171 auto addAnimationsForProperty = [&](const Vector<LayerPropertyAnimation*>& animations, AnimatedPropertyID property) {
3172 if (animations.isEmpty()) {
3173 addBaseValueTransformAnimation(property);
3174 return;
3175 }
3176
3177 LayerPropertyAnimation* earliestAnimation = nullptr;
3178 Vector<RefPtr<PlatformCAAnimation>> caAnimations;
3179 for (auto* animation : WTF::makeReversedRange(animations)) {
3180 if (auto beginTime = animation->computedBeginTime()) {
3181 if (!earliestAnimation || *earliestAnimation->computedBeginTime() > *beginTime)
3182 earliestAnimation = animation;
3183 }
3184 prepareAnimationForAddition(*animation);
3185 caAnimations.append(animation->m_animation);
3186 }
3187
3188 // If we have an animation with an explicit begin time that does not fill backwards and starts with a delay,
3189 // we must create a non-interpolating animation to set the current value for this transform-related property
3190 // until that animation begins.
3191 if (earliestAnimation) {
3192 auto fillMode = earliestAnimation->m_animation->fillMode();
3193 if (fillMode != PlatformCAAnimation::Backwards && fillMode != PlatformCAAnimation::Both) {
3194 Seconds earliestBeginTime = *earliestAnimation->computedBeginTime() + animationGroupBeginTime;
3195 if (earliestBeginTime > currentTime) {
3196 if (auto* baseValueTransformAnimation = makeBaseValueTransformAnimation(property, TransformationMatrixSource::AskClient, earliestBeginTime)) {
3197 prepareAnimationForAddition(*baseValueTransformAnimation);
3198 caAnimations.append(baseValueTransformAnimation->m_animation);
3199 }
3200 }
3201 }
3202 }
3203
3204 addAnimationGroup(property, caAnimations);
3205 };
3206
3207 addAnimationsForProperty(transformAnimations, AnimatedPropertyTransform);
3208 addAnimationsForProperty(scaleAnimations, AnimatedPropertyScale);
3209 addAnimationsForProperty(rotateAnimations, AnimatedPropertyRotate);
3210 addAnimationsForProperty(translateAnimations, AnimatedPropertyTranslate);
3211 }
3212}

3341bool GraphicsLayerCA::createAnimationFromKeyframes(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const Animation* animation, const String& animationName, Seconds timeOffset, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3342{

3346
3347 bool additive = false;

3352 if (isKeyframe(valueList)) {
3353 caAnimation = createKeyframeAnimation(animation, propertyIdToString(valueList.property()), additive, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3354 valuesOK = setAnimationKeyframes(valueList, animation, caAnimation.get(), keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3355 } else {
3356 if (animation->timingFunction()->isSpringTimingFunction())
3357 caAnimation = createSpringAnimation(animation, propertyIdToString(valueList.property()), additive, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3358 else
3359 caAnimation = createBasicAnimation(animation, propertyIdToString(valueList.property()), additive, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3360 valuesOK = setAnimationEndpoints(valueList, animation, caAnimation.get());
3361 }
3362
3363 if (!valuesOK)
3364 return false;
3365
3366 m_animations.append(LayerPropertyAnimation(caAnimation.releaseNonNull(), animationName, valueList.property(), animationIndex, 0, timeOffset));
3367
3368 return true;
3369}

3371bool GraphicsLayerCA::appendToUncommittedAnimations(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const TransformOperations* operations, const Animation* animation, const String& animationName, const FloatSize& boxSize, int animationIndex, Seconds timeOffset, bool isMatrixAnimation, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3372{

3374

3376 bool validMatrices = true;

3379 validMatrices = setTransformAnimationKeyframes(valueList, animation, caAnimation.get(), animationIndex, transformOp, isMatrixAnimation, boxSize, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3380 } else {
3381 if (animation->timingFunction()->isSpringTimingFunction())
3382 caAnimation = createSpringAnimation(animation, propertyIdToString(valueList.property()), false, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3383 else
3384 caAnimation = createBasicAnimation(animation, propertyIdToString(valueList.property()), false, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3385 validMatrices = setTransformAnimationEndpoints(valueList, animation, caAnimation.get(), animationIndex, transformOp, isMatrixAnimation, boxSize);
3386 }
3387
3388 if (!validMatrices)
