3395bool GraphicsLayerCA::createTransformAnimationsFromKeyframes(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const Animation* animation, const String& animationName, Seconds timeOffset, const FloatSize& boxSize, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3396{
3397 ASSERT(animatedPropertyIsTransformOrRelated(valueList.property()));
3398
3399 bool hasBigRotation;
3400 int listIndex = validateTransformOperations(valueList, hasBigRotation);
3401 const TransformOperations* operations = (listIndex >= 0) ? &static_cast<const TransformAnimationValue&>(valueList.at(listIndex)).value() : 0;
3402
3403 bool validMatrices = true;
3404
3405 // If function lists don't match we do a matrix animation, otherwise we do a component hardware animation.
3406 bool isMatrixAnimation = valueList.property() == AnimatedPropertyTransform ? listIndex < 0 : true;
3407 int numAnimations = isMatrixAnimation ? 1 : operations->size();
3408
3409 for (int animationIndex = 0; animationIndex < numAnimations; ++animationIndex) {
3410 if (!appendToUncommittedAnimations(valueList, operations, animation, animationName, boxSize, animationIndex, timeOffset, isMatrixAnimation, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)) {
3411 validMatrices = false;
3412 break;
3413 }
3414 }
3415
3416 return validMatrices;
3417}
3418
3419bool GraphicsLayerCA::appendToUncommittedAnimations(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const FilterOperation* operation, const Animation* animation, const String& animationName, int animationIndex, Seconds timeOffset, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3420{
3421 FilterOperation::OperationType filterOp = operation->type();
3422 int numAnimatedProperties = PlatformCAFilters::numAnimatedFilterProperties(filterOp);
3423
3424 // Each filter might need to animate multiple properties, each with their own keyPath. The keyPath is always of the form:
3425 //
3426 // filter.filter_<animationIndex>.<filterPropertyName>
3427 //
3428 // PlatformCAAnimation tells us how many properties each filter has and we iterate that many times and create an animation
3429 // for each. This internalFilterPropertyIndex gets passed to PlatformCAAnimation so it can properly create the property animation
3430 // values.
3431 for (int internalFilterPropertyIndex = 0; internalFilterPropertyIndex < numAnimatedProperties; ++internalFilterPropertyIndex) {
3432 bool valuesOK;
3433 RefPtr<PlatformCAAnimation> caAnimation;
3434 auto keyPath = makeString("filters.filter_", animationIndex, '.', PlatformCAFilters::animatedFilterPropertyName(filterOp, internalFilterPropertyIndex));
3435
3436 if (isKeyframe(valueList)) {
3437 caAnimation = createKeyframeAnimation(animation, keyPath, false, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3438 valuesOK = setFilterAnimationKeyframes(valueList, animation, caAnimation.get(), animationIndex, internalFilterPropertyIndex, filterOp, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3439 } else {
3440 caAnimation = createBasicAnimation(animation, keyPath, false, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction);
3441 valuesOK = setFilterAnimationEndpoints(valueList, animation, caAnimation.get(), animationIndex, internalFilterPropertyIndex);
3442 }
3443
3444 ASSERT(valuesOK);
3445
3446 m_animations.append(LayerPropertyAnimation(caAnimation.releaseNonNull(), animationName, valueList.property(), animationIndex, internalFilterPropertyIndex, timeOffset));
3447 }
3448
3449 return true;
3450}
3451
3452bool GraphicsLayerCA::createFilterAnimationsFromKeyframes(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const Animation* animation, const String& animationName, Seconds timeOffset, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3453{
3454#if ENABLE(FILTERS_LEVEL_2)
3455 ASSERT(valueList.property() == AnimatedPropertyFilter || valueList.property() == AnimatedPropertyWebkitBackdropFilter);
3456#else
3457 ASSERT(valueList.property() == AnimatedPropertyFilter);
3458#endif
3459
3460 int listIndex = validateFilterOperations(valueList);
3461 if (listIndex < 0)
3462 return false;
3463
3464 const FilterOperations& operations = static_cast<const FilterAnimationValue&>(valueList.at(listIndex)).value();
3465 // Make sure the platform layer didn't fallback to using software filter compositing instead.
3466 if (!filtersCanBeComposited(operations))
3467 return false;
3468
3469 int numAnimations = operations.size();
3470
3471 // FIXME: We can't currently hardware animate shadows.
3472 for (int i = 0; i < numAnimations; ++i) {
3473 if (operations.at(i)->type() == FilterOperation::DROP_SHADOW)
3474 return false;
3475 }
3476
3477 for (int animationIndex = 0; animationIndex < numAnimations; ++animationIndex) {
3478 if (!appendToUncommittedAnimations(valueList, operations.operations().at(animationIndex).get(), animation, animationName, animationIndex, timeOffset, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction))
3479 return false;
3480 }
3481
3482 return true;
3483}

3505
3506void GraphicsLayerCA::setupAnimation(PlatformCAAnimation* propertyAnim, const Animation* anim, bool additive, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3507{
3508 double duration = anim->duration();
3509 if (duration <= 0)
3510 duration = cAnimationAlmostZeroDuration;
3511
3512 float repeatCount = anim->iterationCount();
3513 if (repeatCount == Animation::IterationCountInfinite)
3514 repeatCount = std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
3515 else if (anim->direction() == Animation::AnimationDirectionAlternate || anim->direction() == Animation::AnimationDirectionAlternateReverse)
3516 repeatCount /= 2;
3517
3518 PlatformCAAnimation::FillModeType fillMode = PlatformCAAnimation::NoFillMode;
3519 switch (anim->fillMode()) {
3520 case AnimationFillMode::None:
3521 fillMode = PlatformCAAnimation::Forwards; // Use "forwards" rather than "removed" because the style system will remove the animation when it is finished. This avoids a flash.
3522 break;
3523 case AnimationFillMode::Backwards:
3524 fillMode = PlatformCAAnimation::Both; // Use "both" rather than "backwards" because the style system will remove the animation when it is finished. This avoids a flash.
3525 break;
3526 case AnimationFillMode::Forwards:
3527 fillMode = PlatformCAAnimation::Forwards;
3528 break;
3529 case AnimationFillMode::Both:
3530 fillMode = PlatformCAAnimation::Both;
3531 break;
3532 }
3533
3534 propertyAnim->setDuration(duration);
3535 propertyAnim->setRepeatCount(repeatCount);
3536 propertyAnim->setAutoreverses(anim->direction() == Animation::AnimationDirectionAlternate || anim->direction() == Animation::AnimationDirectionAlternateReverse);
3537 propertyAnim->setRemovedOnCompletion(false);
3538 propertyAnim->setAdditive(additive);
3539 propertyAnim->setFillMode(fillMode);
3540
3541 // FIXME: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=215918
3542 // A CSS Transition is the only scenario where Animation::property() will have
3543 // its mode set to SingleProperty. In this case, we don't set the animation-wide
3544 // timing function to work around a Core Animation limitation.
3545 if (!keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3546 propertyAnim->setTimingFunction(anim->timingFunction());
3547}
3548
3549const TimingFunction& GraphicsLayerCA::timingFunctionForAnimationValue(const AnimationValue& animValue, const Animation& anim, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3550{
3551 if (keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction && anim.timingFunction()) {
3552 // FIXME: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=215918
3553 // A CSS Transition is the only scenario where Animation::property() will have
3554 // its mode set to SingleProperty. In this case, we chose not to set set the
3555 // animation-wide timing function, so we set it on the single keyframe interval
3556 // to work around a Core Animation limitation.
3557 return *anim.timingFunction();
3558 }
3559 if (animValue.timingFunction())
3560 return *animValue.timingFunction();
3561 if (anim.defaultTimingFunctionForKeyframes())
3562 return *anim.defaultTimingFunctionForKeyframes();
3563 return LinearTimingFunction::sharedLinearTimingFunction();
3564}

3576 basicAnim->setToValue(static_cast<const FloatAnimationValue&>(valueList.at(toIndex)).value());

3587bool GraphicsLayerCA::setAnimationKeyframes(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const Animation* animation, PlatformCAAnimation* keyframeAnim, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3588{
3589 Vector<float> keyTimes;
3590 Vector<float> values;
3591 Vector<const TimingFunction*> timingFunctions;
3592
3593 bool forwards = animation->directionIsForwards();
3594
3595 for (unsigned i = 0; i < valueList.size(); ++i) {
3596 unsigned index = forwards ? i : (valueList.size() - i - 1);
3597 const AnimationValue& curValue = valueList.at(index);
3598 keyTimes.append(forwards ? curValue.keyTime() : (1 - curValue.keyTime()));
3599
3600 switch (valueList.property()) {
3601 case AnimatedPropertyOpacity: {
3602 const FloatAnimationValue& floatValue = static_cast<const FloatAnimationValue&>(curValue);
3603 values.append(floatValue.value());
3604 break;
3605 }
3606 default:
3607 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED(); // we don't animate color yet
3608 break;
3609 }
3610
3611 if (i < (valueList.size() - 1))
3612 timingFunctions.append(&timingFunctionForAnimationValue(forwards ? curValue : valueList.at(index - 1), *animation, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction));
3613 }
3614
3615 keyframeAnim->setKeyTimes(keyTimes);
3616 keyframeAnim->setValues(values);
3617 keyframeAnim->setTimingFunctions(timingFunctions, !forwards);
3618
3619 return true;
3620}

3622bool GraphicsLayerCA::setTransformAnimationEndpoints(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const Animation* animation, PlatformCAAnimation* basicAnim, int functionIndex, TransformOperation::OperationType transformOpType, bool isMatrixAnimation, const FloatSize& boxSize)
3623{
3624 ASSERT(valueList.size() == 2);
3625
3626 bool forwards = animation->directionIsForwards();
3627
3628 unsigned fromIndex = !forwards;
3629 unsigned toIndex = forwards;
3630
3631 auto& startValue = static_cast<const TransformAnimationValue&>(valueList.at(fromIndex));
3632 auto& endValue = static_cast<const TransformAnimationValue&>(valueList.at(toIndex));
3633
3634 if (isMatrixAnimation) {
3635 TransformationMatrix fromTransform, toTransform;
3636 startValue.value().apply(boxSize, fromTransform);
3637 endValue.value().apply(boxSize, toTransform);
3638
3639 // If any matrix is singular, CA won't animate it correctly. So fall back to software animation
3640 if (!fromTransform.isInvertible() || !toTransform.isInvertible())
3641 return false;
3642
3643 basicAnim->setFromValue(fromTransform);
3644 basicAnim->setToValue(toTransform);
3645 } else {
3646 if (isTransformTypeNumber(transformOpType)) {
3647 float fromValue;
3648 getTransformFunctionValue(startValue.value().at(functionIndex), transformOpType, boxSize, fromValue);
3649 basicAnim->setFromValue(fromValue);
3650
3651 float toValue;
3652 getTransformFunctionValue(endValue.value().at(functionIndex), transformOpType, boxSize, toValue);
3653 basicAnim->setToValue(toValue);
3654 } else if (isTransformTypeFloatPoint3D(transformOpType)) {
3655 FloatPoint3D fromValue;
3656 getTransformFunctionValue(startValue.value().at(functionIndex), transformOpType, boxSize, fromValue);
3657 basicAnim->setFromValue(fromValue);
3658
3659 FloatPoint3D toValue;
3660 getTransformFunctionValue(endValue.value().at(functionIndex), transformOpType, boxSize, toValue);
3661 basicAnim->setToValue(toValue);
3662 } else {
3663 TransformationMatrix fromValue;
3664 getTransformFunctionValue(startValue.value().at(functionIndex), transformOpType, boxSize, fromValue);
3665 basicAnim->setFromValue(fromValue);
3666
3667 TransformationMatrix toValue;
3668 getTransformFunctionValue(endValue.value().at(functionIndex), transformOpType, boxSize, toValue);
3669 basicAnim->setToValue(toValue);
3670 }
3671 }
3672
3673 auto valueFunction = getValueFunctionNameForTransformOperation(transformOpType);
3674 if (valueFunction != PlatformCAAnimation::NoValueFunction)
3675 basicAnim->setValueFunction(valueFunction);
3676
3677 return true;
3678}
3679
3680bool GraphicsLayerCA::setTransformAnimationKeyframes(const KeyframeValueList& valueList, const Animation* animation, PlatformCAAnimation* keyframeAnim, int functionIndex, TransformOperation::OperationType transformOpType, bool isMatrixAnimation, const FloatSize& boxSize, bool keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction)
3681{
3682 Vector<float> keyTimes;
3683 Vector<float> floatValues;
3684 Vector<FloatPoint3D> floatPoint3DValues;
3685 Vector<TransformationMatrix> transformationMatrixValues;
3686 Vector<const TimingFunction*> timingFunctions;
3687
3688 bool forwards = animation->directionIsForwards();
3689
3690 for (unsigned i = 0; i < valueList.size(); ++i) {
3691 unsigned index = forwards ? i : (valueList.size() - i - 1);
3692 const TransformAnimationValue& curValue = static_cast<const TransformAnimationValue&>(valueList.at(index));
3693 keyTimes.append(forwards ? curValue.keyTime() : (1 - curValue.keyTime()));
3694
3695 TransformationMatrix transform;
3696
3697 if (isMatrixAnimation) {
3698 curValue.value().apply(boxSize, transform);
3699
3700 // If any matrix is singular, CA won't animate it correctly. So fall back to software animation
3701 if (!transform.isInvertible())
3702 return false;
3703
3704 transformationMatrixValues.append(transform);
3705 } else {
3706 const TransformOperation* transformOp = curValue.value().at(functionIndex);
3707 if (isTransformTypeNumber(transformOpType)) {
3708 float value;
3709 getTransformFunctionValue(transformOp, transformOpType, boxSize, value);
3710 floatValues.append(value);
3711 } else if (isTransformTypeFloatPoint3D(transformOpType)) {
3712 FloatPoint3D value;
3713 getTransformFunctionValue(transformOp, transformOpType, boxSize, value);
3714 floatPoint3DValues.append(value);
3715 } else {
3716 TransformationMatrix value;
3717 getTransformFunctionValue(transformOp, transformOpType, boxSize, value);
3718 transformationMatrixValues.append(value);
3719 }
3720
3721 curValue.value().apply(boxSize, transform);
3722 }
3723
3724 if (i < (valueList.size() - 1))
3725 timingFunctions.append(&timingFunctionForAnimationValue(forwards ? curValue : valueList.at(index - 1), *animation, keyframesShouldUseAnimationWideTimingFunction));
3726 }
3727
3728 keyframeAnim->setKeyTimes(keyTimes);
3729
3730 if (isTransformTypeNumber(transformOpType))
3731 keyframeAnim->setValues(floatValues);
3732 else if (isTransformTypeFloatPoint3D(transformOpType))
3733 keyframeAnim->setValues(floatPoint3DValues);
3734 else
3735 keyframeAnim->setValues(transformationMatrixValues);
3736
3737 keyframeAnim->setTimingFunctions(timingFunctions, !forwards);
3738
3739 PlatformCAAnimation::ValueFunctionType valueFunction = getValueFunctionNameForTransformOperation(transformOpType);
3740 if (valueFunction != PlatformCAAnimation::NoValueFunction)
3741 keyframeAnim->setValueFunction(valueFunction);
3742
3743 return true;
3744}

4222void GraphicsLayerCA::changeLayerTypeTo(PlatformCALayer::LayerType newLayerType)
4223{
4224 PlatformCALayer::LayerType oldLayerType = m_layer->layerType();
4225 if (newLayerType == oldLayerType)
4226 return;
4227
4228 bool wasTiledLayer = oldLayerType == PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeTiledBackingLayer;
4229 bool isTiledLayer = newLayerType == PlatformCALayer::LayerTypeTiledBackingLayer;
4230
4231 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> oldLayer = m_layer;
4232 m_layer = createPlatformCALayer(newLayerType, this);
4233
4234 m_usingBackdropLayerType = isCustomBackdropLayerType(newLayerType);
4235
4236 m_layer->adoptSublayers(*oldLayer);
4237
4238#ifdef VISIBLE_TILE_WASH
4239 if (m_visibleTileWashLayer)
4240 m_layer->appendSublayer(*m_visibleTileWashLayer;
4241#endif
4242
4243 if (isMaskLayer()) {
4244 // A mask layer's superlayer is the layer that it masks. Set the MaskLayerChanged dirty bit
4245 // so that the parent will fix up the platform layers in commitLayerChangesAfterSublayers().
4246 if (GraphicsLayer* parentLayer = parent())
4247 downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*parentLayer).noteLayerPropertyChanged(MaskLayerChanged);
4248 } else if (oldLayer->superlayer()) {
4249 // Skip this step if we don't have a superlayer. This is probably a benign
4250 // case that happens while restructuring the layer tree, and also occurs with
4251 // WebKit2 page overlays, which can become tiled but are out-of-tree.
4252 oldLayer->superlayer()->replaceSublayer(*oldLayer, *m_layer);
4253 }
4254
4255 addUncommittedChanges(ChildrenChanged
4256 | GeometryChanged
4257 | TransformChanged
4258 | ChildrenTransformChanged
4259 | MasksToBoundsChanged
4260 | ContentsOpaqueChanged
4261 | BackfaceVisibilityChanged
4262 | BackgroundColorChanged
4263 | ContentsScaleChanged
4264 | AcceleratesDrawingChanged
4265 | SupportsSubpixelAntialiasedTextChanged
4266 | FiltersChanged
4267 | BackdropFiltersChanged
4268 | MaskLayerChanged
4269 | OpacityChanged
4270 | EventRegionChanged
4271 | NameChanged
4272 | DebugIndicatorsChanged);
4273
4274 if (isTiledLayer)
4275 addUncommittedChanges(CoverageRectChanged);
4276
4277 moveAnimations(oldLayer.get(), m_layer.get());
4278
4279 // need to tell new layer to draw itself
4280 setNeedsDisplay();
4281
4282 if (wasTiledLayer || isTiledLayer)
4283 client().tiledBackingUsageChanged(this, isTiledLayer);
4284}

4312RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> GraphicsLayerCA::findOrMakeClone(CloneID cloneID, PlatformCALayer *sourceLayer, LayerMap& clones, CloneLevel cloneLevel)
4313{
4314 if (!sourceLayer)
4315 return nullptr;
4316
4317 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> resultLayer;
4318
4319 // Add with a dummy value to get an iterator for the insertion position, and a boolean that tells
4320 // us whether there's an item there. This technique avoids two hash lookups.
4321 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> dummy;
4322 LayerMap::AddResult addResult = clones.add(cloneID, dummy);
4323 if (!addResult.isNewEntry) {
4324 // Value was not added, so it exists already.
4325 resultLayer = addResult.iterator->value.get();
4326 } else {
4327 resultLayer = cloneLayer(sourceLayer, cloneLevel);
4328#if ENABLE(TREE_DEBUGGING)
4329 resultLayer->setName(makeString("clone ", cloneID[0U], " of ", sourceLayer->layerID()));
4330#else
4331 resultLayer->setName("clone of " + m_name);
4332#endif
4333 addResult.iterator->value = resultLayer;
4334 }
4335
4336 return resultLayer;
4337}

4392void GraphicsLayerCA::propagateLayerChangeToReplicas(ScheduleFlushOrNot scheduleFlush)
4393{
4394 for (GraphicsLayer* currentLayer = this; currentLayer; currentLayer = currentLayer->parent()) {
4395 GraphicsLayerCA& currentLayerCA = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*currentLayer);
4396 if (!currentLayerCA.hasCloneLayers())
4397 break;
4398
4399 if (currentLayerCA.replicaLayer())
4400 downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*currentLayerCA.replicaLayer()).noteLayerPropertyChanged(ReplicatedLayerChanged, scheduleFlush);
4401 }
4402}
4403
4404RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> GraphicsLayerCA::fetchCloneLayers(GraphicsLayer* replicaRoot, ReplicaState& replicaState, CloneLevel cloneLevel)
4405{
4406 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> primaryLayer;
4407 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> structuralLayer;
4408 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> contentsLayer;
4409 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> contentsClippingLayer;
4410 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> contentsShapeMaskLayer;
4411 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> shapeMaskLayer;
4412 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> backdropLayer;
4413 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> backdropClippingLayer;
4414 ensureCloneLayers(replicaState.cloneID(), primaryLayer, structuralLayer, contentsLayer, contentsClippingLayer, contentsShapeMaskLayer, shapeMaskLayer, backdropLayer, backdropClippingLayer, cloneLevel);
4415
4416 if (m_maskLayer) {
4417 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> maskClone = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*m_maskLayer).fetchCloneLayers(replicaRoot, replicaState, IntermediateCloneLevel);
4418 primaryLayer->setMask(maskClone.get());
4419 }
4420
4421 if (m_replicatedLayer) {
4422 // We are a replica being asked for clones of our layers.
4423 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> replicaRoot = replicatedLayerRoot(replicaState);
4424 if (!replicaRoot)
4425 return nullptr;
4426
4427 if (structuralLayer) {
4428 structuralLayer->insertSublayer(*replicaRoot, 0);
4429 return structuralLayer;
4430 }
4431
4432 primaryLayer->insertSublayer(*replicaRoot, 0);
4433 return primaryLayer;
4434 }
4435
4436 auto& childLayers = children();
4437 Vector<RefPtr<PlatformCALayer>> clonalSublayers;
4438
4439 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> replicaLayer;
4440
4441 if (m_replicaLayer && m_replicaLayer != replicaRoot) {
4442 // We have nested replicas. Ask the replica layer for a clone of its contents.
4443 replicaState.setBranchType(ReplicaState::ReplicaBranch);
4444 replicaLayer = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(*m_replicaLayer).fetchCloneLayers(replicaRoot, replicaState, RootCloneLevel);
4445 replicaState.setBranchType(ReplicaState::ChildBranch);
4446 }
4447
4448 if (contentsClippingLayer && contentsLayer) {
4449 contentsClippingLayer->appendSublayer(*contentsLayer);
4450 }
4451
4452 if (contentsShapeMaskLayer)
4453 contentsClippingLayer->setMask(contentsShapeMaskLayer.get());
4454
4455 if (shapeMaskLayer)
4456 primaryLayer->setMask(shapeMaskLayer.get());
4457
4458 if (replicaLayer || structuralLayer || contentsLayer || contentsClippingLayer || childLayers.size() > 0) {
4459 if (structuralLayer) {
4460 if (backdropLayer) {
4461 clonalSublayers.append(backdropLayer);
4462 backdropLayer->setMask(backdropClippingLayer.get());
4463 }
4464
4465 // Replicas render behind the actual layer content.
4466 if (replicaLayer)
4467 clonalSublayers.append(replicaLayer);
4468
4469 // Add the primary layer next. Even if we have negative z-order children, the primary layer always comes behind.
4470 clonalSublayers.append(primaryLayer);
4471 } else if (contentsClippingLayer) {
4472 // FIXME: add the contents layer in the correct order with negative z-order children.
4473 // This does not cause visible rendering issues because currently contents layers are only used
4474 // for replaced elements that don't have children.
4475 clonalSublayers.append(contentsClippingLayer);
4476 } else if (contentsLayer) {
4477 // FIXME: add the contents layer in the correct order with negative z-order children.
4478 // This does not cause visible rendering issues because currently contents layers are only used
4479 // for replaced elements that don't have children.
4480 clonalSublayers.append(contentsLayer);
4481 }
4482
4483 replicaState.push(ReplicaState::ChildBranch);
4484
4485 for (auto& childLayer : childLayers) {
4486 GraphicsLayerCA& childLayerCA = downcast<GraphicsLayerCA>(childLayer.get());
4487 if (auto platformLayer = childLayerCA.fetchCloneLayers(replicaRoot, replicaState, IntermediateCloneLevel))
4488 clonalSublayers.append(WTFMove(platformLayer));
4489 }
4490
4491 replicaState.pop();
4492
4493 for (size_t i = 0; i < clonalSublayers.size(); ++i)
4494 clonalSublayers[i]->removeFromSuperlayer();
4495 }
4496
4497 RefPtr<PlatformCALayer> result;
4498 if (structuralLayer) {
4499 structuralLayer->setSublayers(clonalSublayers);
4500
4501 if (contentsClippingLayer || contentsLayer) {
4502 // If we have a transform layer, then the contents layer is parented in the
4503 // primary layer (which is itself a child of the transform layer).
4504 primaryLayer->removeAllSublayers();
4505 primaryLayer->appendSublayer(contentsClippingLayer ? *contentsClippingLayer : *contentsLayer);
4506 }
4507
4508 result = structuralLayer;
4509 } else {
4510 primaryLayer->setSublayers(clonalSublayers);
4511 result = primaryLayer;
4512 }
4513
4514 return result;
4515}

4517Ref<PlatformCALayer> GraphicsLayerCA::cloneLayer(PlatformCALayer *layer, CloneLevel cloneLevel)
4518{
4519 auto newLayer = layer->clone(this);
4520
4521 if (cloneLevel == IntermediateCloneLevel) {
4522 newLayer->setOpacity(layer->opacity());
4523 copyAnimations(layer, newLayer.ptr());
4524 }
4525
4526 setLayerDebugBorder(newLayer, cloneLayerDebugBorderColor(isShowingDebugBorder()), cloneLayerBorderWidth);
4527
4528 return newLayer;
4529}
4530
4531void GraphicsLayerCA::updateOpacityOnLayer()
4532{
4533 primaryLayer()->setOpacity(m_opacity);
4534
4535 if (LayerMap* layerCloneMap = primaryLayerClones()) {
4536 for (auto& clone : *layerCloneMap) {
4537 if (m_replicaLayer && isReplicatedRootClone(clone.key))
4538 continue;
4539
4540 clone.value->setOpacity(m_opacity);
4541 }
4542 }
4543
4544#if ENABLE(MODEL_ELEMENT)

4560void GraphicsLayerCA::computePixelAlignment(float pageScale, const FloatPoint& positionRelativeToBase,
4561 FloatPoint& position, FloatPoint3D& anchorPoint, FloatSize& alignmentOffset) const
4562{
4563 FloatRect baseRelativeBounds(positionRelativeToBase, m_size);
4564 FloatRect scaledBounds = baseRelativeBounds;
4565 float contentsScale = pageScale * deviceScaleFactor();
4566 // Scale by the page scale factor to compute the screen-relative bounds.
4567 scaledBounds.scale(contentsScale);
4568 // Round to integer boundaries.
4569 FloatRect alignedBounds = encloseRectToDevicePixels(LayoutRect(scaledBounds), deviceScaleFactor());
4570
4571 // Convert back to layer coordinates.
4572 alignedBounds.scale(1 / contentsScale);
4573
4574 alignmentOffset = baseRelativeBounds.location() - alignedBounds.location();
4575 position = m_position - alignmentOffset;
4576
4577 // Now we have to compute a new anchor point which compensates for rounding.
4578 float anchorPointX = m_anchorPoint.x();
4579 float anchorPointY = m_anchorPoint.y();
4580
4581 if (alignedBounds.width())
4582 anchorPointX = (baseRelativeBounds.width() * anchorPointX + alignmentOffset.width()) / alignedBounds.width();
4583
4584 if (alignedBounds.height())
4585 anchorPointY = (baseRelativeBounds.height() * anchorPointY + alignmentOffset.height()) / alignedBounds.height();
4586
4587 anchorPoint = FloatPoint3D(anchorPointX, anchorPointY, m_anchorPoint.z() * contentsScale);
4588}

4596void GraphicsLayerCA::addUncommittedChanges(LayerChangeFlags flags)
4597{
4598 m_uncommittedChanges |= flags;
4599
4600 if (m_isCommittingChanges)
4601 return;
4602
4603 for (auto* ancestor = parent(); ancestor; ancestor = ancestor->parent()) {
4604 auto& ancestorCA = static_cast<GraphicsLayerCA&>(*ancestor);
4605 ASSERT(!ancestorCA.m_isCommittingChanges);
4606 if (ancestorCA.hasDescendantsWithUncommittedChanges())
4607 return;
4608 ancestorCA.setHasDescendantsWithUncommittedChanges(true);
4609 }
4610}

4618{

4624 addUncommittedChanges(flags);

4633double GraphicsLayerCA::backingStoreMemoryEstimate() const
4634{
4635 if (!drawsContent())
4636 return 0;
4637
4638 // contentsLayer is given to us, so we don't really know anything about its contents.
4639 // FIXME: ignores layer clones.
4640
4641 if (TiledBacking* tiledBacking = this->tiledBacking())
4642 return tiledBacking->retainedTileBackingStoreMemory();
4643
4644 if (!backingStoreAttached())
4645 return 0;
4646
4647 return m_layer->backingStoreBytesPerPixel() * size().width() * m_layer->contentsScale() * size().height() * m_layer->contentsScale();
4648}
